(Of course, there's a catch.)

261
00:08:47,224 --> 00:08:48,453
- What is it?
- What's going on?

262
00:08:48,454 --> 00:08:50,023
- What are you up to now?
- Wait.

263
00:08:50,024 --> 00:08:52,054
- Before that...
- Wait. Let's switch places.

264
00:08:52,654 --> 00:08:55,224
- Hold on.
- There's another car. Why?

265
00:08:55,464 --> 00:08:56,763
Before that...

266
00:08:56,764 --> 00:08:58,393
(Where will this car be headed to?)

267
00:08:58,394 --> 00:08:59,634
Before that...

268
00:09:01,134 --> 00:09:02,163
Joon.

269
00:09:02,164 --> 00:09:03,204
- What's going on?
- What?

270
00:09:03,774 --> 00:09:05,404
What? I didn't do anything.

271
00:09:05,674 --> 00:09:08,174
Joon, you can't join us.

272
00:09:08,674 --> 00:09:10,044
- Seon Ho must've picked him.
- All right.

273
00:09:10,114 --> 00:09:11,613
- Now, - I bet he summoned you.

274
00:09:11,614 --> 00:09:12,813
you must leave.

275
00:09:12,814 --> 00:09:14,013
Seon Ho must have picked him!

276
00:09:14,014 --> 00:09:15,713
- I bet he's angry.
- Seon Ho chose you!

277
00:09:15,714 --> 00:09:17,013
(He's dragged by force.)

278
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:20,454
- Isn't she lovely?
- My gosh.

279
00:09:20,784 --> 00:09:21,853
Isn't she lovely?

280
00:09:21,854 --> 00:09:23,893
(He was dreaming of freely traveling Namhae.)

281
00:09:23,894 --> 00:09:24,894
- Gosh.
- Oh, my.

282
00:09:24,895 --> 00:09:27,063
- Seon Ho must've picked him.
- He must be angry.

283
00:09:27,064 --> 00:09:29,064
- Seon Ho must be infuriated.
- Yes. Seon Ho...

284
00:09:29,424 --> 00:09:31,034
- Go ahead.
- Bye.

285
00:09:31,334 --> 00:09:32,764
- Bye.
- Are you serious?

286
00:09:32,894 --> 00:09:34,203
Seon Ho must have chosen you!

287
00:09:34,204 --> 00:09:36,104
- Wait. What's going on?
- He must be infuriated.

288
00:09:36,264 --> 00:09:37,434
What's going on?

289
00:09:37,804 --> 00:09:40,003
Seon Ho chose Joon...

290
00:09:40,004 --> 00:09:41,143
- He picked Joon.
- That's right.

291
00:09:41,144 --> 00:09:42,844
- as his partner to share his fate.
- He summoned Joon.

292
00:09:43,074 --> 00:09:44,743
- He's going to catch cuttlefish?
- Yes, he'll join Seon Ho.

293
00:09:44,744 --> 00:09:46,543
(The fated partners who will get on the cuttlefish boat)

294
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:48,784
(The fated partners who will get on the cuttlefish boat)

295
00:09:49,314 --> 00:09:50,314
Congratulations.

296
00:09:50,315 --> 00:09:53,483
(It was a few minutes ago when he found out about his fate.)

297
00:09:53,484 --> 00:09:55,124
- But...
- But?

298
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:59,593
they need one more person to join the cuttlefish boat.

299
00:09:59,594 --> 00:10:00,624
Of course.

300
00:10:01,624 --> 00:10:02,994
Who will you take?

301
00:10:04,594 --> 00:10:05,764
I can just pick one of them?

302
00:10:05,894 --> 00:10:07,063
It depends on my decision?

303
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,064
(Clueless of their fate)

304
00:10:09,304 --> 00:10:10,333
Gosh, who should I pick?

305
00:10:10,334 --> 00:10:11,334
(Thinking hard)

306
00:10:11,335 --> 00:10:13,244
Joon and I had breakfast together.

307
00:10:13,504 --> 00:10:15,544
Se Yoon and I caught webfoot octopus together.

308
00:10:16,504 --> 00:10:18,114
I'll go with Joon.

309
00:10:19,144 --> 00:10:20,343
- I got it.
- Okay.

310
00:10:20,344 --> 00:10:21,344
(Seon Ho picks Joon.)

311
00:10:21,944 --> 00:10:23,383
We had breakfast this morning.

312
00:10:23,384 --> 00:10:25,053
(Reason: They had breakfast together.)

313
00:10:25,054 --> 00:10:26,653
- That's the reason?
- Yes. No other reason.

314
00:10:26,654 --> 00:10:29,124
(Reason: They had breakfast together.)

315
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:30,894
Come on, Seon Ho.

316
00:10:32,694 --> 00:10:34,193
I didn't think we were that close.

317
00:10:34,194 --> 00:10:35,194
(Why did he pick me?)

318
00:10:35,195 --> 00:10:37,233
I didn't know we were close enough for him to pick me.

319
00:10:37,234 --> 00:10:38,693
(Engulfed by anger, he denies his friendship.)

320
00:10:38,694 --> 00:10:39,904
This is too mean.

321
00:10:41,234 --> 00:10:42,604
You must be curious where we're going.

322
00:10:42,764 --> 00:10:44,404
- Aren't I going fishing?
- Right.

323
00:10:45,704 --> 00:10:48,073
Joon, you were chosen as an additional member...

324
00:10:48,074 --> 00:10:49,843
to catch cuttlefish.

325
00:10:49,844 --> 00:10:51,143
(Joon is chosen as an additional member...)

326
00:10:51,144 --> 00:10:52,414
(to catch cuttlefish.)

327
00:10:53,914 --> 00:10:56,144
Come on. I don't think I'll say anything when I get there.

328
00:10:57,854 --> 00:11:00,454
Seriously. I had a 25-percent chance.

329
00:11:04,254 --> 00:11:05,624
Will the three of them just rest?

330
00:11:06,494 --> 00:11:08,364
Will they really rest? Like they're on a holiday?

331
00:11:09,024 --> 00:11:10,293
- What are we going to do?
- What will we do?

332
00:11:10,294 --> 00:11:11,694
- We...
- The three of you can freely...

333
00:11:12,164 --> 00:11:14,203
travel Namhae for real.

334
00:11:14,204 --> 00:11:15,264
- But...
- Really?

335
00:11:15,334 --> 00:11:17,833
If you need money, we can give it to you.

336
00:11:17,834 --> 00:11:19,273
The others will work to pay it back.

337
00:11:19,274 --> 00:11:21,203
(When they spend money, they will have to pay it back.)

338
00:11:21,204 --> 00:11:22,243
- Really?
- What?

339
00:11:22,244 --> 00:11:23,913
You can spend as much money as they earn.

340
00:11:23,914 --> 00:11:25,573
- We're rich. Cuttlefish are pricey.
- Let's do this!

341
00:11:25,574 --> 00:11:27,043
- But hold on.
- Let's spend it all.

342
00:11:27,044 --> 00:11:28,414
- Let's spend 5,000 dollars.
- Yes.

343
00:11:29,584 --> 00:11:30,854
Let's go and look at some land.

344
00:11:31,454 --> 00:11:33,083
- You know? Let's buy land.
- So they never leave.

345
00:11:33,084 --> 00:11:34,084
Yes.

346
00:11:34,084 --> 00:11:35,084
(They're happy at the thought of spending money.)

347
00:11:35,085 --> 00:11:37,554
Are there some activities we can enjoy here?

348
00:11:37,754 --> 00:11:39,353
- We need to enjoy our holiday.
- But...

349
00:11:39,354 --> 00:11:40,863
- Activities?
- Activities.

350
00:11:40,864 --> 00:11:42,393
Well, we can do that. What's that called?

351
00:11:42,394 --> 00:11:43,763
We don't need a big one, though.

352
00:11:43,764 --> 00:11:45,494
- The coastal road is beautiful.
- Yes.

353
00:11:45,694 --> 00:11:46,763
Let's go for a drive.

354
00:11:46,764 --> 00:11:49,504
They have that thing here. What do you call that?

355
00:11:50,134 --> 00:11:51,203
- A bicycle?
- A scooter?

356
00:11:51,204 --> 00:11:52,573
- An electric bike.
- An electric bike.

357
00:11:52,574 --> 00:11:53,574
- They have it here?
- Really?

358
00:11:53,575 --> 00:11:54,904
Bamboo Fishing Weir...

359
00:11:55,404 --> 00:11:58,013
We can drive it around the coastal road nearby.

360
00:11:58,014 --> 00:11:59,043
That's nice.

361
00:11:59,044 --> 00:12:00,243
- Let's go there.
- Let's go.

362
00:12:00,244 --> 00:12:02,183
- Off to the Bamboo Fishing Weir.
- Let's go there.

363
00:12:02,184 --> 00:12:04,284
- Well...
- Do you need an allowance?

364
00:12:04,514 --> 00:12:05,653
- Give us some money.
- Yes.

365
00:12:05,654 --> 00:12:07,724
- You need to give us money.
- We need a lot of money.

366
00:12:07,984 --> 00:12:09,483
You must consider our social position here.

367
00:12:09,484 --> 00:12:11,294
- How much do you need?
- About 700 dollars.

368
00:12:11,424 --> 00:12:12,424
You need 700 dollars?

369
00:12:12,425 --> 00:12:14,394
- Cuttlefish are expensive.
- Of course.

370
00:12:14,564 --> 00:12:16,464
You always ask this when you already have a price in your mind.

371
00:12:16,864 --> 00:12:18,734
- Start us off with 200 dollars.
- So 200 dollars?

372
00:12:19,294 --> 00:12:21,104
- We can ask for more later.
- Let's do 50 dollars each.

373
00:12:21,664 --> 00:12:22,834
- Here.
- Two hundred dollars.

374
00:12:23,004 --> 00:12:25,133
Okay. No. It's not that I don't trust you.

375
00:12:25,134 --> 00:12:26,134
You're counting the bills?

376
00:12:26,774 --> 00:12:28,743
- He really gave us 200 dollars?
- My gosh.

377
00:12:28,744 --> 00:12:29,744
(Checking the bills in case they're conned)

378
00:12:30,244 --> 00:12:32,673
- Okay.
- If you end up going to work next,

379
00:12:32,674 --> 00:12:34,814
don't pick me. Let me rest.

380
00:12:35,184 --> 00:12:36,714
- We can't promise that.
- But...

381
00:12:36,854 --> 00:12:38,514
You can't expect to rest here.

382
00:12:39,454 --> 00:12:40,723
Enjoy your holiday!

383
00:12:40,724 --> 00:12:41,824
- Thanks!
- Okay.

384
00:12:42,154 --> 00:12:43,154
Okay.

385
00:12:43,454 --> 00:12:44,454
Holiday!

386
00:12:44,455 --> 00:12:46,893
It might be our last clip together. Let's say goodbye together.

387
00:12:46,894 --> 00:12:48,093
Holiday

388
00:12:48,094 --> 00:12:49,523
We'll be gone one at a time.

389
00:12:49,524 --> 00:12:51,033
(You never know when you'll be dragged to work.)

390
00:12:51,034 --> 00:12:52,064
Wave at them.

391
00:12:53,134 --> 00:12:55,204
Okay. Let's go and ride the electric bike.

392
00:12:56,264 --> 00:12:58,734
- Let's get a cool drink too.
- Let's get some coffee.

393
00:12:59,074 --> 00:13:00,104
This is great.

394
00:13:01,174 --> 00:13:03,643
I'm expecting the waves to be rough today.

395
00:13:03,644 --> 00:13:05,044
(The boat comes into view.)

396
00:13:06,844 --> 00:13:09,943
(He arrives at the port for the cuttlefish fishing trip.)

397
00:13:09,944 --> 00:13:11,654
You said it was a holiday!

398
00:13:12,914 --> 00:13:16,324
(Welcome to working holiday.)

399
00:13:16,894 --> 00:13:19,994
(It's a tough reality to face.)

400
00:13:20,364 --> 00:13:21,364
Thank you.

401
00:13:21,624 --> 00:13:24,734
(Mijo Port, 7:30am)

402
00:13:24,994 --> 00:13:27,334
What's going on? It's only 7:30am.

403
00:13:27,664 --> 00:13:29,163
I woke up, washed my hair, and had breakfast.

404
00:13:29,164 --> 00:13:30,604
But I'm getting on a boat to catch cuttlefish.

405
00:13:30,974 --> 00:13:32,804
(Is it possible that I'm still sleeping?)

406
00:13:33,304 --> 00:13:34,574
It's beautiful, though.

407
00:13:35,144 --> 00:13:37,614
(Around that time, Joon's car pulls into Mijo Port.)

408
00:13:37,774 --> 00:13:39,914
Seon Ho must be waiting for me. Right?

409
00:13:41,444 --> 00:13:42,744
Look at him waving.

410
00:13:44,854 --> 00:13:46,384
He's so clueless.

411
00:13:47,824 --> 00:13:49,353
I'm not in a good mood.

412
00:13:49,354 --> 00:13:50,354
(Cluelessly sipping on his drink)

413
00:13:51,454 --> 00:13:53,664
(You brat, Seon Ho!)

414
00:13:53,994 --> 00:13:56,724
(The anger in his gait is detected even from afar.)

415
00:13:57,064 --> 00:13:59,664
My gosh, I can see it in his face. He's super angry.

416
00:14:00,134 --> 00:14:02,063
You're super angry.

417
00:14:02,064 --> 00:14:03,133
(Dropping his bag)

418
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:05,104
- You're so angry.
- What are you doing?

419
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:07,444
Why me?

420
00:14:08,004 --> 00:14:09,504
We had breakfast together.

421
00:14:10,244 --> 00:14:11,414
I had no other reason.

422
00:14:11,574 --> 00:14:13,374
That's even more annoying. He had no other reason.

423
00:14:14,214 --> 00:14:15,344
What is this?

424
00:14:15,584 --> 00:14:17,654
- I...
- Come on. What is this?

425
00:14:18,414 --> 00:14:21,324
(At the quayside,)

426
00:14:21,824 --> 00:14:24,894
(a man is waiting for them restlessly.)

427
00:14:25,254 --> 00:14:27,864
Hurry up! It's over here!

428
00:14:28,124 --> 00:14:29,824
Okay.

429
00:14:30,294 --> 00:14:31,294
Let's go.

430
00:14:31,364 --> 00:14:33,534
- He's asking us to hurry.
- Then you must hurry.

431
00:14:33,864 --> 00:14:35,034
Why me?

432
00:14:35,504 --> 00:14:37,004
Why did it have to be me?

433
00:14:37,304 --> 00:14:38,534
Because I like you.

434
00:14:38,874 --> 00:14:39,903
Hello.

435
00:14:39,904 --> 00:14:41,173
- Hello.
- Hello.

436
00:14:41,174 --> 00:14:42,343
Nice to meet you. I'm the captain.

437
00:14:42,344 --> 00:14:43,344
Nice to meet you.

438
00:14:43,345 --> 00:14:45,044
- Hello. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

439
00:14:45,374 --> 00:14:46,843
Let's get out there to catch some cuttlefish.

440
00:14:46,844 --> 00:14:48,784
- Let's get going.
- Yes. Let's head out.

441
00:14:48,984 --> 00:14:49,984
I can't believe this.

442
00:14:49,985 --> 00:14:51,383
It's my first time getting sent to work like this...

443
00:14:51,384 --> 00:14:53,014
as soon as we begin.

444
00:14:56,124 --> 00:14:58,694
(Sailing out into deep waters)

445
00:14:59,024 --> 00:15:00,054
You know what?

446
00:15:01,024 --> 00:15:02,493
It's not so bad since the weather is nice.

447
00:15:02,494 --> 00:15:03,834
- Right. The weather is good.
- My gosh.

448
00:15:04,094 --> 00:15:06,194
- Imagine if we came in winter.
- My gosh.

449
00:15:06,294 --> 00:15:09,534
Don't think of this as a fishing boat.

450
00:15:10,104 --> 00:15:11,104
Think of it as a yacht.

451
00:15:11,105 --> 00:15:12,174
- It'd be so great.
- Right.

452
00:15:12,504 --> 00:15:14,444
We can eat some raw cuttlefish here.

453
00:15:14,804 --> 00:15:15,844
Right.

454
00:15:15,944 --> 00:15:18,273
Fresh seafood right on the boat tastes amazing.

455
00:15:18,274 --> 00:15:19,274
(Let's be positive.)

456
00:15:19,275 --> 00:15:20,344
Of course.

457
00:15:21,184 --> 00:15:22,843
- If you think about that...
- I wanted to eat with you.

458
00:15:22,844 --> 00:15:23,853
So I called you.

459
00:15:23,854 --> 00:15:26,084
(We'll be able to return safely, right?)

460
00:15:27,184 --> 00:15:29,254
- I feel bad and grateful.
- Right.

461
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,993
It's been so long...

462
00:15:31,994 --> 00:15:35,064
since we felt this free on the show. Right?

463
00:15:35,224 --> 00:15:37,594
- We're traveling freely for real.
- Right.

464
00:15:37,864 --> 00:15:40,234
Let's ride the electric bike along the coast first.

465
00:15:40,334 --> 00:15:41,533
- The coastal road?
- By the time we're done,

466
00:15:41,534 --> 00:15:43,003
cafes will start to open.

467
00:15:43,004 --> 00:15:44,334
- Right.
- By then, they should be open.

468
00:15:44,804 --> 00:15:45,904
Gosh, those guys...

469
00:15:46,534 --> 00:15:49,344
Catching cuttlefish in the morning will be tough.

470
00:15:49,474 --> 00:15:50,943
Isn't this the first time for any of us...

471
00:15:50,944 --> 00:15:52,374
to be sent to work right after the opening segment?

472
00:15:52,774 --> 00:15:54,414
- Exactly.
- Right. It is.

473
00:15:54,784 --> 00:15:56,043
I love it here.

474
00:15:56,044 --> 00:15:58,283
- I want to slow down even more.
- The road...

475
00:15:58,284 --> 00:15:59,854
- It's so beautiful.
- Yes. The road is...

476
00:16:00,054 --> 00:16:02,353
- so beautiful.
- What a great way to relax.

477
00:16:02,354 --> 00:16:04,123
(The view of Namhae makes them want to stay longer on the road.)

478
00:16:04,124 --> 00:16:05,153
This is it.

479
00:16:05,154 --> 00:16:06,323
- Where?
- Here.

480
00:16:06,324 --> 00:16:07,724
The rental shop is right here.

481
00:16:08,294 --> 00:16:09,694
- It's pretty big too.
- Yes.

482
00:16:10,294 --> 00:16:11,564
- Let's go and spend it all!
- Let's go.

483
00:16:11,664 --> 00:16:13,604
Let's just have fun today and eat good food. Okay?

484
00:16:14,164 --> 00:16:15,763
- Yes. Let's show the viewers...
- Jong Min.

485
00:16:15,764 --> 00:16:17,033
- what flexing is all about.
- Okay.

486
00:16:17,034 --> 00:16:18,403
(Excited to spend all the money they have today)

487
00:16:18,404 --> 00:16:19,573
- You know what?
- Let's go.

488
00:16:19,574 --> 00:16:21,044
- Hello.
- Hello.

489
00:16:21,374 --> 00:16:22,374
- Gosh.
- Hello.

490
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,844
You must have seafood soup or something. Was it ramyeon?

491
00:16:25,244 --> 00:16:26,643
We sell ramyeon here.

492
00:16:26,644 --> 00:16:27,744
- You do?
- I see.

493
00:16:27,984 --> 00:16:29,983
(I knew it. You can't fool my nose.)

494
00:16:29,984 --> 00:16:32,413
- We're in paradise. Okay.
- My gosh.

495
00:16:32,414 --> 00:16:33,483
- Hold on.
- All right.

496
00:16:33,484 --> 00:16:34,683
- What?
- Let's take a look.

497
00:16:34,684 --> 00:16:36,883
- Should we grab a drink?
- Let's get a drink.

498
00:16:36,884 --> 00:16:38,224
I actually needed one.

499
00:16:38,524 --> 00:16:40,693
- Baby Monster.
- Yes.

500
00:16:40,694 --> 00:16:41,694
- I want to work hard today.
- Okay.

501
00:16:41,694 --> 00:16:42,694
Okay. Get one.

502
00:16:42,695 --> 00:16:43,864
I'll get the sports drink!

503
00:16:44,434 --> 00:16:45,494
Okay.

504
00:16:45,934 --> 00:16:47,733
But the cup noodles do look good.

505
00:16:47,734 --> 00:16:51,434
They do. But let's come back for ramyeon after brunch.

506
00:16:51,904 --> 00:16:53,233
- Three.
- Three.

507
00:16:53,234 --> 00:16:54,243
We'll take three bikes.

508
00:16:54,244 --> 00:16:56,404
You're going to pay cash, right?

509
00:16:56,704 --> 00:16:58,014
- We'll give you a discount.
- Okay.

510
00:16:58,614 --> 00:17:00,214
It's 88.5 dollars.

511
00:17:00,614 --> 00:17:02,044
It's 88.5 dollars?

512
00:17:02,444 --> 00:17:04,814
- Seon Ho. Joon. Thank you!
- Yes.

513
00:17:05,984 --> 00:17:08,684
Here's the million-dollar question. Do you have a 4XL helmet?

514
00:17:09,084 --> 00:17:10,653
We've never had a customer...

515
00:17:10,654 --> 00:17:12,253
whose head didn't fit into our helmets.

516
00:17:12,254 --> 00:17:13,663
He's never found a helmet in his size.

517
00:17:13,664 --> 00:17:15,164
- Really?
- He's never found the right one.

518
00:17:15,294 --> 00:17:16,423
Let's just...

519
00:17:16,424 --> 00:17:18,134
(Let's see.)

520
00:17:18,764 --> 00:17:19,993
(It fits perfectly.)

521
00:17:19,994 --> 00:17:21,103
- All right.
- It's big, right?

522
00:17:21,104 --> 00:17:22,934
- This is pretty good.
- What?

523
00:17:23,634 --> 00:17:25,333
We wear a lot of helmets when we play games.

524
00:17:25,334 --> 00:17:26,704
Let's buy two helmets for me.

525
00:17:27,374 --> 00:17:29,103
Let's buy them here. I must buy the ones that fit me.

526
00:17:29,104 --> 00:17:30,444
- The helmets fit.
- Excuse me.

527
00:17:31,014 --> 00:17:32,343
How do you extend this?

528
00:17:32,344 --> 00:17:33,744
- Let me help.
- Okay. Thank you.

529
00:17:33,884 --> 00:17:35,483
Gosh, it rarely fits Se Yoon's head.

530
00:17:35,484 --> 00:17:37,054
It looks pretty good on you.

531
00:17:37,214 --> 00:17:39,484
- This is good.
- The strap is actually long for me.

532
00:17:39,854 --> 00:17:41,783
- It's long for me.
- Get their number.

533
00:17:41,784 --> 00:17:43,183
- Order more helmets later.
- Okay.

534
00:17:43,184 --> 00:17:44,223
- These helmets? Okay.
- Yes.

535
00:17:44,224 --> 00:17:45,993
Just buy some now. Ask them for the price.

536
00:17:45,994 --> 00:17:47,364
- Let's buy one.
- Yes.

537
00:17:47,594 --> 00:17:48,923
- We'll head out now.
- Okay.

538
00:17:48,924 --> 00:17:50,023
- Have fun.
- Thank you.

539
00:17:50,024 --> 00:17:51,164
Thank you.

540
00:17:51,334 --> 00:17:53,163
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

541
00:17:53,164 --> 00:17:55,364
- Let's go! Here we go.
- Let's go.

542
00:17:55,734 --> 00:17:58,104
- Let's go. Hi.
- I can't believe this

543
00:17:58,274 --> 00:18:00,204
(Let's ride the bike along the coast now!)

544
00:18:00,474 --> 00:18:01,573
(I can't believe this)

545
00:18:01,574 --> 00:18:04,014
(It's so great in Namhae)

546
00:18:05,514 --> 00:18:09,484
(The weather in Namhae is crazy!)

547
00:18:11,084 --> 00:18:12,253
(Enjoying)

548
00:18:12,254 --> 00:18:13,254
This is great.

549
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:14,683
How great is this?

550
00:18:14,684 --> 00:18:15,923
(Summoning Dae Gil from "The Slave Hunters")

551
00:18:15,924 --> 00:18:17,824
- You're so loud.
- He's so loud.

552
00:18:18,054 --> 00:18:19,993
How great is Namhae?

553
00:18:19,994 --> 00:18:21,623
(Jong Min and his juniors are captivated by the view.)

554
00:18:21,624 --> 00:18:22,994
This is great.

555
00:18:23,324 --> 00:18:25,394
Look at the ocean on your right.

556
00:18:25,764 --> 00:18:28,264
This is the highlight of Namhae.

557
00:18:28,764 --> 00:18:30,303
This is nice. Oh, I love it.

558
00:18:30,304 --> 00:18:32,303
The only thing I can do is comment on how nice this is.

559
00:18:32,304 --> 00:18:33,704
(The vast ocean brings out a series of compliments.)

560
00:18:34,374 --> 00:18:36,944
Seon Ho. Joon. Thank you!

561
00:18:37,214 --> 00:18:40,114
We're having a great time thanks to you guys!

562
00:18:40,584 --> 00:18:42,014
What a relaxing trip this is.

563
00:18:42,084 --> 00:18:43,544
It's so beautiful here.

564
00:18:44,214 --> 00:18:45,454
It's stunning.

565
00:18:46,454 --> 00:18:47,924
Hey, it's for jukbang anchovies.

566
00:18:48,524 --> 00:18:49,754
- It's crazy.
- Look at that.

567
00:18:50,084 --> 00:18:51,424
- Is that for jukbang anchovies?
- Look over there.

568
00:18:51,554 --> 00:18:53,894
They put up nets to catch anchovies.

569
00:18:54,694 --> 00:18:55,923
It's so far.

570
00:18:55,924 --> 00:18:57,433
(As they enjoy their ride...)

571
00:18:57,434 --> 00:19:00,934
Gosh, I think we're getting close to our destination.

572
00:19:01,204 --> 00:19:02,664
Look on your left.

573
00:19:03,564 --> 00:19:04,933
It's a photo spot.

574
00:19:04,934 --> 00:19:06,674
Look on your left. It's a photo spot.

575
00:19:06,934 --> 00:19:08,603
Should we take a photo on the swing?

576
00:19:08,604 --> 00:19:09,644
Yes.

577
00:19:09,844 --> 00:19:11,444
All right. Let's stop here.

578
00:19:11,974 --> 00:19:13,244
We can park it here.

579
00:19:14,344 --> 00:19:16,244
- One of us should sit.
- Right.

580
00:19:16,444 --> 00:19:18,614
And one of us should stand there.

581
00:19:19,484 --> 00:19:22,584
One, two, three.

582
00:19:23,084 --> 00:19:24,594
(We're so happy!)

583
00:19:24,794 --> 00:19:27,264
One, two, three.

584
00:19:27,964 --> 00:19:28,993
Okay.

585
00:19:28,994 --> 00:19:30,893
(Creating another beautiful memory in Namhae)

586
00:19:30,894 --> 00:19:32,493
I'm hungry. Is there any food?

587
00:19:32,494 --> 00:19:34,533
- I see a snack bar over there.
- There's a snack bar.

588
00:19:34,534 --> 00:19:35,733
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

589
00:19:35,734 --> 00:19:37,274
- Hello.
- Can we buy food here?

590
00:19:37,674 --> 00:19:38,674
- All right.
- Okay.

591
00:19:39,104 --> 00:19:40,544
Of course, Jong Min. This is a snack bar.

592
00:19:40,974 --> 00:19:43,304
- I want this.
- Oh, snacks.

593
00:19:44,644 --> 00:19:46,043
- You should...
- You guys...

594
00:19:46,044 --> 00:19:47,843
- should get one too.
- Grab whatever you want.

595
00:19:47,844 --> 00:19:49,213
Get a drink or something. Don't feel bad.

596
00:19:49,214 --> 00:19:51,154
- Or grab some snacks. It's on us.
- Yes.

597
00:19:51,484 --> 00:19:52,484
- Come on.
- You...

598
00:19:52,485 --> 00:19:54,354
- Grab one.
- We're all family here.

599
00:19:55,484 --> 00:19:56,523
(The snack bar gets crowded in no time.)

600
00:19:56,524 --> 00:19:58,153
- Our pronunciation was precise.
- Everyone, come on in.

601
00:19:58,154 --> 00:19:59,554
- Oh, I bet they want jjondeugi.
- Come here.

602
00:19:59,724 --> 00:20:01,664
(Piles of snacks and drinks)

603
00:20:02,524 --> 00:20:04,764
They're really going all out here.

604
00:20:04,864 --> 00:20:06,194
- This is too much.
- You know?

605
00:20:06,334 --> 00:20:07,964
- Can I buy firecrackers?
- Firecrackers?

606
00:20:09,204 --> 00:20:11,034
Why are you buying firecrackers here?

607
00:20:11,374 --> 00:20:12,934
We don't want to waste...

608
00:20:13,674 --> 00:20:15,044
What do you want?

609
00:20:15,474 --> 00:20:16,973
What if someone were to come in and attack us?

610
00:20:16,974 --> 00:20:18,273
- What...
- Even our security team is here.

611
00:20:18,274 --> 00:20:19,644
What are you doing here?

612
00:20:21,114 --> 00:20:22,744
- We bought way too much food.
- Thank you.

613
00:20:23,314 --> 00:20:25,454
Look at the snacks. My goodness.

614
00:20:26,214 --> 00:20:28,453
Other members are making money for us.

615
00:20:28,454 --> 00:20:29,523
- You know this saying?
- What?

616
00:20:29,524 --> 00:20:31,524
"Some only make money. Some only spend money."

617
00:20:31,754 --> 00:20:33,623
"Some only clean up. Some only make a mess."

618
00:20:33,624 --> 00:20:35,823
The number is going up aggressively.

619
00:20:35,824 --> 00:20:36,824
Go ahead.

620
00:20:37,164 --> 00:20:39,393
- How much is it?
- It's 76 dollars.

621
00:20:39,394 --> 00:20:41,404
This should cover it, right?

622
00:20:42,064 --> 00:20:43,064
It's so relaxing.

623
00:20:43,065 --> 00:20:44,503
This is how one ought to travel Namhae.

624
00:20:44,504 --> 00:20:47,244
You're indeed old. You like jjondeugi.

625
00:20:47,444 --> 00:20:49,404
Seriously. This is the right way to enjoy life.

626
00:20:49,904 --> 00:20:50,974
A relaxing life.

627
00:20:51,574 --> 00:20:53,273
Let's make them work today.

628
00:20:53,274 --> 00:20:54,284
- Yes.
- Okay.

629
00:20:54,414 --> 00:20:55,984
And let's lie to them.

630
00:20:56,514 --> 00:20:58,984
If we tell them we bought food for the staff,

631
00:20:59,714 --> 00:21:01,654
- it might upset them.
- Yes.

632
00:21:01,884 --> 00:21:03,653
Let's tell them we lost the games.

633
00:21:03,654 --> 00:21:04,654
Yes.

634
00:21:05,024 --> 00:21:07,124
You're an evil genius, seriously.

635
00:21:08,124 --> 00:21:10,323
It's so good since I'm not paying for this.

636
00:21:10,324 --> 00:21:11,394
It's good.

637
00:21:11,564 --> 00:21:12,693
Thank you.

638
00:21:12,694 --> 00:21:14,203
(Is he thanking them or teasing them?)

639
00:21:14,204 --> 00:21:15,234
I'll enjoy this.

640
00:21:15,704 --> 00:21:16,934
- It's huge.
- Wait.

641
00:21:17,504 --> 00:21:18,934
- This is it?
- What? Did you get lucky?

642
00:21:19,234 --> 00:21:20,234
This is it.

643
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:23,174
- It's what Joon must be catching.
- The cuttlefish?

644
00:21:23,404 --> 00:21:24,814
It's what Seon Ho must be catching.

645
00:21:25,344 --> 00:21:27,614
(The cuttlefish is right here.)

646
00:21:28,284 --> 00:21:30,554
We're traveling in style thanks to the cuttlefish.

647
00:21:31,084 --> 00:21:32,583
Let's get coffee. It's time for coffee.

648
00:21:32,584 --> 00:21:34,154
I love having coffee in the morning.

649
00:21:34,654 --> 00:21:36,884
We should get a rich one with a lot of cream.

650
00:21:37,594 --> 00:21:39,693
- One that costs over 10 dollars.
- That sounds great.

651
00:21:39,694 --> 00:21:41,763
- Let's go.
- Let's go and get coffee.

652
00:21:41,764 --> 00:21:43,364
(They set out again to buy coffee.)

653
00:21:43,494 --> 00:21:44,864
We're going pretty far.

654
00:21:45,534 --> 00:21:47,304
If we keep going, we'll reach Jeju Island.

655
00:21:47,704 --> 00:21:49,834
Gosh, we're here!

656
00:21:49,993 --> 00:21:52,023
Gosh, we're here!

657
00:21:52,293 --> 00:21:53,363
Let's go!

658
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:55,992
- I see. They marked the spot.
- It's a buoy.

659
00:21:55,993 --> 00:21:57,062
I see.

660
00:21:57,063 --> 00:21:58,862
They hooked a net here.

661
00:21:58,863 --> 00:21:59,863
I see.

662
00:21:59,864 --> 00:22:01,673
- Should we begin now?
- Yes.

663
00:22:02,403 --> 00:22:05,672
You just need to remove the cuttlefish from the net.

664
00:22:05,673 --> 00:22:07,342
- We just have to pull them out.
- That's all we have to do?

665
00:22:07,343 --> 00:22:09,042
- That's right.
- It will be easy then.

666
00:22:09,043 --> 00:22:10,483
If we try to pull the net, we could get hurt.

667
00:22:10,683 --> 00:22:12,883
- Why don't you try that later?
- Okay.

668
00:22:13,653 --> 00:22:14,752
(The cuttlefish harvest begins.)

669
00:22:14,753 --> 00:22:16,113
He's getting ready.

670
00:22:16,513 --> 00:22:18,883
(The machine starts spinning.)

671
00:22:19,823 --> 00:22:21,053
It's coming up.

672
00:22:21,253 --> 00:22:23,223
(The net is pulled up by the machine.)

673
00:22:24,223 --> 00:22:25,462
Is that a halibut?

674
00:22:25,463 --> 00:22:26,823
- It's a flounder.
- A flounder.

675
00:22:26,993 --> 00:22:28,093
The spring flounder.

676
00:22:28,293 --> 00:22:30,063
You can start working now.

677
00:22:30,233 --> 00:22:32,063
- How do we do it?
- It's expensive.

678
00:22:32,133 --> 00:22:33,403
Do we just cut it?

679
00:22:34,173 --> 00:22:35,202
(Grab the fish firmly.)

680
00:22:35,203 --> 00:22:36,203
Grab it.

681
00:22:37,073 --> 00:22:38,442
It's just like catching shrimp.

682
00:22:38,443 --> 00:22:40,312
(Cut the tangled net and pull it out.)

683
00:22:40,313 --> 00:22:41,313
Right.

684
00:22:41,314 --> 00:22:43,012
(Easy peasy, right?)

685
00:22:43,013 --> 00:22:44,082
You can put it over there.

686
00:22:44,083 --> 00:22:45,083
- Okay.
- Where?

687
00:22:45,813 --> 00:22:47,113
- Put it in there?
- Yes.

688
00:22:51,623 --> 00:22:52,983
(Catch the flounder!)

689
00:22:53,923 --> 00:22:54,953
What are you doing?

690
00:22:55,893 --> 00:22:57,962
When I cover their eyes, fish can relax.

691
00:22:57,963 --> 00:22:59,762
- I see. Really?
- I have to cover the eyes.

692
00:22:59,763 --> 00:23:00,962
- I'm serious.
- It's relaxed now.

693
00:23:00,963 --> 00:23:02,262
It's relaxed. It's not moving.

694
00:23:02,263 --> 00:23:03,263
Remove your hands.

695
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:04,662
- See? It's moving now.
- Yes. It's moving.

696
00:23:04,663 --> 00:23:05,732
- I learned that.
- Right.

697
00:23:05,733 --> 00:23:06,833
You have to cover their eyes.

698
00:23:07,133 --> 00:23:08,633
It's like putting on a blindfold.

699
00:23:09,473 --> 00:23:11,402
- Hey. It's a flounder. What?
- This is a tongue sole.

700
00:23:11,403 --> 00:23:13,473
A tongue sole? Grilled tongue sole is tasty.

701
00:23:13,913 --> 00:23:15,043
Try it.

702
00:23:16,113 --> 00:23:17,583
All right. I got you.

703
00:23:18,083 --> 00:23:20,613
(Covering its eyes again)

704
00:23:20,783 --> 00:23:22,913
Removing the fish from the net is harder than I thought.

705
00:23:23,583 --> 00:23:26,252
(Covering the eyes and placing it inside the bucket)

706
00:23:26,253 --> 00:23:29,292
(The first fish from Joon's harvest)

707
00:23:29,293 --> 00:23:30,362
It's a monkfish.

708
00:23:30,363 --> 00:23:31,693
- Gosh, that's a monkfish?
- A monkfish?

709
00:23:31,963 --> 00:23:33,892
- It's a monkfish.
- Gosh, it looks scary.

710
00:23:33,893 --> 00:23:35,433
- It's good in a salad.
- It's small. I must let it go.

711
00:23:35,993 --> 00:23:38,133
(Releasing it back into the ocean as it's too small)

712
00:23:38,233 --> 00:23:39,962
(I'll tell you a story how Joon almost caught me.)

713
00:23:39,963 --> 00:23:42,872
We're not catching as many cuttlefish as I thought we would.

714
00:23:42,873 --> 00:23:45,143
- Right. There aren't that many.
- Cuttlefish must be rare. Right?

715
00:23:45,673 --> 00:23:47,172
We used to catch a lot of them.

716
00:23:47,173 --> 00:23:48,472
- It's hard to catch them now.
- I see.

717
00:23:48,473 --> 00:23:49,942
Why is it hard to catch them nowadays?

718
00:23:49,943 --> 00:23:52,543
It's due to changes in water temperature and other factors.

719
00:23:52,713 --> 00:23:55,552
Then the price of cuttlefish must be very high.

720
00:23:55,553 --> 00:23:57,183
(The catch of cuttlefish has decreased for various reasons.)

721
00:23:58,053 --> 00:23:59,423
It's very slippery.

722
00:23:59,683 --> 00:24:01,823
- It's wild flatfish.
- Flatfish is delicious.

723
00:24:02,693 --> 00:24:04,593
(By the way...)

724
00:24:04,763 --> 00:24:07,363
(When will we catch cuttlefish, captain?)

725
00:24:07,963 --> 00:24:09,233
There's a cuttlefish.

726
00:24:09,563 --> 00:24:11,402
There it is.

727
00:24:11,403 --> 00:24:12,432
(A cuttlefish finally appeared.)

728
00:24:12,433 --> 00:24:13,433
There's a cuttlefish.

729
00:24:14,433 --> 00:24:15,603
There it is.

730
00:24:16,773 --> 00:24:17,843
- Gosh.
- It's big.

731
00:24:18,003 --> 00:24:19,673
- It's huge.
- It's very big.

732
00:24:20,173 --> 00:24:22,912
(They catch their first cuttlefish.)

733
00:24:22,913 --> 00:24:25,413
If you drop this cuttlefish, it will squirt ink.

734
00:24:25,543 --> 00:24:26,613
We have to cover its eyes.

735
00:24:27,213 --> 00:24:29,153
Here in the front...

736
00:24:29,283 --> 00:24:30,653
- Do we cut it like that?
- Yes.

737
00:24:30,753 --> 00:24:32,382
By the way, it's very chubby.

738
00:24:32,383 --> 00:24:33,723
Why is it so fat?

739
00:24:33,953 --> 00:24:36,292
It's probably because it gained weight.

740
00:24:36,293 --> 00:24:37,493
- Because it gained weight?
- It gained weight?

741
00:24:37,523 --> 00:24:39,493
- Do cuttlefish also gain weight?
- It's just like Se Yoon.

742
00:24:40,093 --> 00:24:41,663
They probably gain weight when they eat a lot.

743
00:24:41,963 --> 00:24:44,203
- It's because it's filled with air.
- Is that why?

744
00:24:45,303 --> 00:24:46,833
Look. It's squirting ink.

745
00:24:48,303 --> 00:24:49,603
It keeps squirting ink.

746
00:24:53,273 --> 00:24:56,972
(Squirting ink refreshingly)

747
00:24:56,973 --> 00:24:58,513
Look, it became black. Did you see that?

748
00:24:59,283 --> 00:25:00,413
It turned black right away.

749
00:25:00,883 --> 00:25:01,913
We caught another one.

750
00:25:02,753 --> 00:25:04,782
We got another one.

751
00:25:04,783 --> 00:25:06,583
(It's also plump.)

752
00:25:06,953 --> 00:25:09,853
(This time, Seon Ho preps the cuttlefish himself.)

753
00:25:10,123 --> 00:25:11,992
- Look how fresh it is.
- It's very fresh.

754
00:25:11,993 --> 00:25:15,093
This part is really hard.

755
00:25:15,633 --> 00:25:16,932
It's because there's a shell inside.

756
00:25:16,933 --> 00:25:18,863
Is the shell like a shield?

757
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:20,203
It's cuttlebone.

758
00:25:20,533 --> 00:25:22,873
(Cuttlefish have a very hard bone.)

759
00:25:22,933 --> 00:25:24,203
It's similar to a turtle.

760
00:25:25,343 --> 00:25:27,243
- It's an octopus.
- We caught an octopus.

761
00:25:28,543 --> 00:25:29,642
It's an octopus.

762
00:25:29,643 --> 00:25:31,512
(They also caught an East Asian common octopus.)

763
00:25:31,513 --> 00:25:32,683
It's an octopus.

764
00:25:33,013 --> 00:25:34,412
- An East Asian common octopus.
- Is that it?

765
00:25:34,413 --> 00:25:35,413
(Fascinated)

766
00:25:36,553 --> 00:25:37,682
It's very strong.

767
00:25:37,683 --> 00:25:39,453
(Their fishing operation is going smoothly.)

768
00:25:39,983 --> 00:25:41,392
- Please be careful.
- Okay.

769
00:25:41,393 --> 00:25:44,793
(Seon Ho tries hauling up the net.)

770
00:25:44,923 --> 00:25:46,523
- Seon Ho, you're doing well.
- Of course.

771
00:25:47,063 --> 00:25:48,833
Okay. You're good at it.

772
00:25:49,263 --> 00:25:50,433
- Aren't I good?
- Yes.

773
00:25:50,663 --> 00:25:54,073
How many more meters of the net do we have to pull?

774
00:25:55,073 --> 00:25:56,932
- About 300m.
- About 300m?

775
00:25:56,933 --> 00:25:58,242
Three hundred meters starting now?

776
00:25:58,243 --> 00:25:59,873
The fishing net is very long.

777
00:26:00,273 --> 00:26:02,373
- It got faster.
- Hurry. Pull quickly.

778
00:26:02,913 --> 00:26:04,343
- You'll get a workout.
- It got faster.

779
00:26:04,613 --> 00:26:06,143
Something is coming up. What's that?

780
00:26:07,183 --> 00:26:08,883
Let there be a big catch.

781
00:26:09,783 --> 00:26:11,953
(Joon takes it out.)

782
00:26:12,653 --> 00:26:14,293
Let there be a big catch.

783
00:26:15,553 --> 00:26:17,563
Pulling up the net takes more strength than expected.

784
00:26:18,463 --> 00:26:19,592
It's much harder than I thought.

785
00:26:19,593 --> 00:26:20,893
(Struggling)

786
00:26:23,793 --> 00:26:25,963
(Soon, he's covered with ink.)

787
00:26:27,603 --> 00:26:29,273
(More allowance)

788
00:26:30,103 --> 00:26:32,003
It's so slippery that I can't grab it.

789
00:26:32,403 --> 00:26:33,942
(Slippery)

790
00:26:33,943 --> 00:26:34,943
I got it.

791
00:26:35,013 --> 00:26:36,343
(More allowance)

792
00:26:36,943 --> 00:26:38,783
(Filling the box more and more with cuttlefish)

793
00:26:39,913 --> 00:26:41,583
The work is hard today.

794
00:26:42,253 --> 00:26:43,682
- This one is big.
- Let me get that.

795
00:26:43,683 --> 00:26:44,752
(Cuttlefish keep coming up.)

796
00:26:44,753 --> 00:26:46,083
This one isn't filled with ink.

797
00:26:46,283 --> 00:26:48,122
Please stay still.

798
00:26:48,123 --> 00:26:49,953
I'll take you off the net.

799
00:26:50,863 --> 00:26:52,623
- Exactly.
- In the ocean...

800
00:26:55,893 --> 00:26:57,832
(Shooting ink)

801
00:26:57,833 --> 00:26:59,363
In the ocean...

802
00:27:00,933 --> 00:27:02,232
(Joon is very surprised by the ink squirt.)

803
00:27:02,233 --> 00:27:04,172
What's wrong? Did it squirt again?

804
00:27:04,173 --> 00:27:06,002
Gosh, I was so startled.

805
00:27:06,003 --> 00:27:07,173
- Did it squirt again?
- Yes.

806
00:27:07,613 --> 00:27:08,843
It really startled me.

807
00:27:09,543 --> 00:27:13,083
They squirt a lot of ink suddenly and all at once.

808
00:27:13,283 --> 00:27:14,512
- What?
- Hold on.

809
00:27:14,513 --> 00:27:16,552
(Flopping down)

810
00:27:16,553 --> 00:27:17,683
This is...

811
00:27:17,923 --> 00:27:19,883
- It's harder than I thought.
- What's wrong with me?

812
00:27:21,193 --> 00:27:22,853
- What?
- Yes.

813
00:27:23,353 --> 00:27:24,393
One second.

814
00:27:26,463 --> 00:27:28,292
- I'll take it out.
- Give me a second.

815
00:27:28,293 --> 00:27:30,333
(Joon seems a bit off.)

816
00:27:30,763 --> 00:27:32,432
The boat is rocking a lot.

817
00:27:32,433 --> 00:27:34,233
(The boat is rocking due to the stronger wind.)

818
00:27:34,503 --> 00:27:35,702
(Swaying)

819
00:27:35,703 --> 00:27:37,872
This is hard. I feel nauseous.

820
00:27:37,873 --> 00:27:40,102
(Seasickness kicks in.)

821
00:27:40,103 --> 00:27:41,543
I'm in trouble. What's wrong with me?

822
00:27:43,913 --> 00:27:44,942
Oh, no.

823
00:27:44,943 --> 00:27:46,113
(In the end)

824
00:27:46,713 --> 00:27:49,883
This makes you totally helpless.

825
00:27:51,883 --> 00:27:52,883
(Exclaiming)

826
00:27:53,223 --> 00:27:54,523
You usually don't get seasick.

827
00:27:54,893 --> 00:27:56,823
I'm having a hard time.

828
00:27:57,253 --> 00:27:59,362
Gosh, I feel terrible.

829
00:27:59,363 --> 00:28:01,333
(There's still a lot to do. Will they be able to finish fishing?)

830
00:28:01,833 --> 00:28:04,632
(Meanwhile, Team Holiday continues their spending spree.)

831
00:28:04,633 --> 00:28:06,763
Jong Min, where we're going now...

832
00:28:07,163 --> 00:28:08,273
Where are we going?

833
00:28:08,573 --> 00:28:11,103
It's known for its amazing view, so we're going there.

834
00:28:11,403 --> 00:28:13,143
But they only sell coffee.

835
00:28:13,803 --> 00:28:15,172
Why don't we buy some bread on our way?

836
00:28:15,173 --> 00:28:16,672
Let's buy some bread and eat it there.

837
00:28:16,673 --> 00:28:17,682
(That's a good idea.)

838
00:28:17,683 --> 00:28:18,843
Let's buy something.

839
00:28:19,443 --> 00:28:20,753
Unfortunately,

840
00:28:21,253 --> 00:28:22,752
you can buy bread at a hotel,

841
00:28:22,753 --> 00:28:24,583
but I don't think we can just walk in and out.

842
00:28:24,983 --> 00:28:26,052
Is it nearby?

843
00:28:26,053 --> 00:28:28,052
It's right next to where we're going.

844
00:28:28,053 --> 00:28:29,193
Then let's stop by.

845
00:28:29,893 --> 00:28:30,993
Yes.

846
00:28:31,223 --> 00:28:32,522
Do you want bread?

847
00:28:32,523 --> 00:28:33,663
(Are they going to a hotel to buy bread?)

848
00:28:34,933 --> 00:28:36,033
Is it a hotel?

849
00:28:36,563 --> 00:28:38,503
Are we getting bread at a hotel?

850
00:28:39,863 --> 00:28:41,972
- Goodness.
- By the way...

851
00:28:41,973 --> 00:28:43,533
(They boldly came to a hotel, but...)

852
00:28:43,703 --> 00:28:45,503
- Can we eat something so fancy?
- Can we go in?

853
00:28:46,003 --> 00:28:47,613
I bet the bread is expensive here.

854
00:28:47,873 --> 00:28:49,112
We can ask for more money.

855
00:28:49,113 --> 00:28:50,243
(Oh, come on. We have money.)

856
00:28:51,383 --> 00:28:52,442
Isn't this place too fancy for us?

857
00:28:52,443 --> 00:28:53,582
(They walk into the hotel pompously.)

858
00:28:53,583 --> 00:28:55,412
Are you going to keep this lei on?

859
00:28:55,413 --> 00:28:56,752
(He's embarrassed by Jong Min's lei.)

860
00:28:56,753 --> 00:28:58,622
- Do we have to come here for bread?
- Yes.

861
00:28:58,623 --> 00:29:00,022
Be quiet, Jong Min. We can afford it.

862
00:29:00,023 --> 00:29:01,893
Now that we're here,

863
00:29:02,323 --> 00:29:04,592
why don't we get brunch instead of bread?

864
00:29:04,593 --> 00:29:05,663
Let's do that.

865
00:29:05,793 --> 00:29:08,693
If we get brunch here, the price will be brutal.

866
00:29:08,933 --> 00:29:11,002
The other guys won't get out of work.

867
00:29:11,003 --> 00:29:12,602
When will we ever get this chance again?

868
00:29:12,603 --> 00:29:14,072
(An unprecedented incident on 2 Days 1 Night)

869
00:29:14,073 --> 00:29:15,233
This is the cafe.

870
00:29:15,573 --> 00:29:16,702
It must be the place.

871
00:29:16,703 --> 00:29:18,303
- This place looks so fancy.
- My gosh.

872
00:29:18,803 --> 00:29:20,102
This place looks so fancy.

873
00:29:20,103 --> 00:29:21,273
Let's go.

874
00:29:21,743 --> 00:29:23,113
- It looks great.
- Look at the crumble buns.

875
00:29:23,773 --> 00:29:25,813
- Jong Min.
- I definitely have to try this.

876
00:29:25,983 --> 00:29:27,713
You'll lend us money, won't you?

877
00:29:28,013 --> 00:29:29,913
- Of course.
- Egg mayo salt bread.

878
00:29:31,023 --> 00:29:32,422
It's their signature croissant.

879
00:29:32,423 --> 00:29:33,752
- Add one signature croissant.
- I want this.

880
00:29:33,753 --> 00:29:34,893
- I want butter with red bean paste.
- Get one.

881
00:29:35,093 --> 00:29:37,052
- I like butter with red bean paste.
- Butter with what?

882
00:29:37,053 --> 00:29:38,122
Butter with red bean paste.

883
00:29:38,123 --> 00:29:40,063
- I like this.
- Let's take a look around.

884
00:29:40,763 --> 00:29:41,763
Look at this.

885
00:29:41,764 --> 00:29:43,063
- I want some of that.
- It's a pastry.

886
00:29:43,593 --> 00:29:45,762
- You should get one sausage pastry.
- Shall I try it?

887
00:29:45,763 --> 00:29:46,903
It looks delicious.

888
00:29:48,673 --> 00:29:50,902
Should we just get this much? I'm scared of the total.

889
00:29:50,903 --> 00:29:52,143
Isn't this enough?

890
00:29:52,243 --> 00:29:54,473
The bread is as expensive as a whole meal.

891
00:29:55,413 --> 00:29:57,313
Be quiet. Who cares about the price?

892
00:29:57,583 --> 00:29:59,513
- Jong Min.
- We have money. You want some jam?

893
00:29:59,613 --> 00:30:02,452
I'm afraid that Joon will become a slave.

894
00:30:02,453 --> 00:30:03,453
No way.

895
00:30:03,454 --> 00:30:05,122
Jong Min, we have to try this.

896
00:30:05,123 --> 00:30:06,722
It's made with garlic from Namhae.

897
00:30:06,723 --> 00:30:07,752
- We have to try that.
- It's garlic from Namhae.

898
00:30:07,753 --> 00:30:08,853
This is famous.

899
00:30:08,953 --> 00:30:10,522
I don't think we'll see...

900
00:30:10,523 --> 00:30:12,423
Seon Ho or Joon until the end of today's shoot.

901
00:30:12,693 --> 00:30:15,563
Shouldn't we try their signature gelato?

902
00:30:15,893 --> 00:30:17,292
Do you want some? Get one.

903
00:30:17,293 --> 00:30:19,433
Can we also get one citron gelato?

904
00:30:19,633 --> 00:30:20,902
The total is...

905
00:30:20,903 --> 00:30:22,572
(What's the total of their chaotic shopping spree?)

906
00:30:22,573 --> 00:30:23,773
Is it 71.5 dollars?

907
00:30:24,543 --> 00:30:25,802
It's a lot.

908
00:30:25,803 --> 00:30:27,273
(The total is 71.5 dollars.)

909
00:30:27,443 --> 00:30:29,313
Here you go. I'll give you 50 cents.

910
00:30:29,913 --> 00:30:31,843
Can I please get the receipt?

911
00:30:32,843 --> 00:30:34,313
Do you have 14 dollars left?

912
00:30:35,183 --> 00:30:36,253
Yes, 14 dollars.

913
00:30:36,513 --> 00:30:39,382
(They already spent close to 200 dollars.)

914
00:30:39,383 --> 00:30:41,692
- Do you want more money?
- Can you give me 100 dollars?

915
00:30:41,693 --> 00:30:43,252
(Yes, give me more.)

916
00:30:43,253 --> 00:30:46,062
It's 9:30am, and we spent almost 200 dollars.

917
00:30:46,063 --> 00:30:47,192
No, we almost spent 300 dollars.

918
00:30:47,193 --> 00:30:48,333
- Did we?
- Yes.

919
00:30:49,363 --> 00:30:50,933
- Here's 100 dollars.
- Okay.

920
00:30:51,433 --> 00:30:53,433
- Why did you accept that?
- I don't know.

921
00:30:54,303 --> 00:30:55,873
He said that he'd give me money.

922
00:30:55,933 --> 00:30:57,472
Jong Min, we need to think this through.

923
00:30:57,473 --> 00:30:59,643
This could backfire on us.

924
00:31:00,003 --> 00:31:01,212
On us instead?

925
00:31:01,213 --> 00:31:03,173
That we have to earn as much as they spend?

926
00:31:04,343 --> 00:31:05,812
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

927
00:31:05,813 --> 00:31:07,913
(For now, they get bread that's worth 71.5 dollars.)

928
00:31:08,713 --> 00:31:10,252
Let's eat some on our way there.

929
00:31:10,253 --> 00:31:14,053
(They set out to eat bread at a cafe with a beautiful view.)

930
00:31:14,793 --> 00:31:17,593
We're sightseeing. This is great.

931
00:31:17,993 --> 00:31:19,393
- Gosh, this is good.
- It's nice.

932
00:31:19,593 --> 00:31:21,893
Looking at the coast makes me feel like I'm traveling. I'm happy.

933
00:31:22,663 --> 00:31:23,893
We're traveling on our own.

934
00:31:23,993 --> 00:31:25,433
- What's this?
- It's a ticket booth.

935
00:31:25,533 --> 00:31:26,732
- It costs money?
- Yes.

936
00:31:26,733 --> 00:31:27,803
- What?
- Okay.

937
00:31:27,903 --> 00:31:29,133
We'll just pay.

938
00:31:29,233 --> 00:31:30,972
- It's 2 dollars.
- It's 2 dollars for each adult.

939
00:31:30,973 --> 00:31:33,503
How many are we? Let's do it with everyone.

940
00:31:33,603 --> 00:31:34,772
- Just the three of us?
- Hey.

941
00:31:34,773 --> 00:31:35,973
- Let's not joke around.
- How much is it?

942
00:31:36,443 --> 00:31:38,143
- It's 6 dollars.
- It's 6 dollars?

943
00:31:38,713 --> 00:31:39,783
Here you go.

944
00:31:40,613 --> 00:31:41,613
Gosh, this is it.

945
00:31:41,614 --> 00:31:43,152
(Where did the members come to?)

946
00:31:43,153 --> 00:31:45,453
- Here it is.
- The color of the sea is beautiful.

947
00:31:46,383 --> 00:31:49,693
(Where you can see the blue sea of Namhae all at once)

948
00:31:50,793 --> 00:31:54,833
(A skywalk with a magnificent view of Namhae)

949
00:31:55,193 --> 00:31:56,432
- Seriously...
- How is it so beautiful?

950
00:31:56,433 --> 00:31:58,063
Look at the color.

951
00:31:58,663 --> 00:32:00,632
It's exactly the color of a sports drink.

952
00:32:00,633 --> 00:32:03,173
(A mysterious hue created by nature)

953
00:32:03,873 --> 00:32:05,442
It's so great to relax like this.

954
00:32:05,443 --> 00:32:06,872
(You feel relaxed just by looking at the blue sea.)

955
00:32:06,873 --> 00:32:08,513
Is it okay to be happy like this?

956
00:32:09,813 --> 00:32:11,713
What was that?

957
00:32:12,083 --> 00:32:13,383
You startled me.

958
00:32:14,283 --> 00:32:16,613
(The charm of the skywalk is its glass floor.)

959
00:32:16,883 --> 00:32:17,922
(This is exciting.)

960
00:32:17,923 --> 00:32:19,482
- Did I scare you?
- I reacted calmly,

961
00:32:19,483 --> 00:32:20,582
but my heart is pounding.

962
00:32:20,583 --> 00:32:22,192
(Se Yoon was genuinely startled.)

963
00:32:22,193 --> 00:32:23,853
I'm so scared that my knees feel weak.

964
00:32:24,053 --> 00:32:25,163
- Gosh.
- You startled me.

965
00:32:26,023 --> 00:32:27,123
This swing is incredible.

966
00:32:27,693 --> 00:32:28,792
(A swing on the skywalk?)

967
00:32:28,793 --> 00:32:29,963
This is really incredible.

968
00:32:31,033 --> 00:32:32,332
Jong Min, get on the swing and eat.

969
00:32:32,333 --> 00:32:33,962
(At the end of the skywalk is a sky swing hanging precariously.)

970
00:32:33,963 --> 00:32:35,103
What is this?

971
00:32:35,533 --> 00:32:37,203
Let's play rock-paper-scissors. Only one person gets on.

972
00:32:37,373 --> 00:32:38,443
My goodness.

973
00:32:38,803 --> 00:32:39,803
It's shaking.

974
00:32:39,804 --> 00:32:41,272
- I absolutely can't do it.
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.

975
00:32:41,273 --> 00:32:42,643
- Only 1 person gets on it.
- Only 1 person.

976
00:32:43,073 --> 00:32:44,613
Forget it. I'm not getting on that.

977
00:32:45,183 --> 00:32:46,612
We have a lot of money. Aren't you going to spend it?

978
00:32:46,613 --> 00:32:47,983
This costs seven dollars.

979
00:32:48,153 --> 00:32:49,412
- Seven dollars? That's a lot.
- Okay.

980
00:32:49,413 --> 00:32:51,222
- I won't do it. It's too expensive.
- Let's have one person do it.

981
00:32:51,223 --> 00:32:52,283
It's too expensive.

982
00:32:53,153 --> 00:32:54,153
(Glancing)

983
00:32:54,154 --> 00:32:55,192
(Making eye contact with the swing as if he was possessed)

984
00:32:55,193 --> 00:32:57,863
I won't do it. I just imagined it.

985
00:32:58,193 --> 00:32:59,963
I imagined myself on the swing. I won't do it.

986
00:33:00,523 --> 00:33:02,933
- Gosh, no way.
- We'll do it here.

987
00:33:03,333 --> 00:33:04,333
Sir.

988
00:33:04,603 --> 00:33:08,703
I weigh 130kg. Can I still get on the swing?

989
00:33:08,873 --> 00:33:10,303
- No.
- Okay!

990
00:33:11,043 --> 00:33:12,772
(Exempted due to his weight of 130kg)

991
00:33:12,773 --> 00:33:14,842
Okay.

992
00:33:14,843 --> 00:33:16,572
Is it okay even if he's 158cm tall?

993
00:33:16,573 --> 00:33:17,782
- That's okay.
- Your height is fine.

994
00:33:17,783 --> 00:33:19,813
I have a disease.

995
00:33:20,383 --> 00:33:22,883
- I suffer from an illness.
- I can stop it whenever you want.

996
00:33:23,113 --> 00:33:24,253
- Really?
- Yes.

997
00:33:24,423 --> 00:33:25,482
Please stop it now.

998
00:33:25,483 --> 00:33:27,453
(Desperate)

999
00:33:27,553 --> 00:33:29,152
Let's play one round of rock-paper-scissors.

1000
00:33:29,153 --> 00:33:30,453
Just one round?

1001
00:33:30,793 --> 00:33:31,823
Seriously?

1002
00:33:32,363 --> 00:33:33,763
- If you lose, you have to get on.
- Sure.

1003
00:33:34,963 --> 00:33:36,393
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

1004
00:33:38,103 --> 00:33:39,163
Did you see that?

1005
00:33:39,903 --> 00:33:41,233
(DinDin will get on the sky swing.)

1006
00:33:41,533 --> 00:33:43,232
Okay, all you have to do is beat me next.

1007
00:33:43,233 --> 00:33:45,603
(He seems happier than being exempted from fishing.)

1008
00:33:46,073 --> 00:33:47,302
This is so scary.

1009
00:33:47,303 --> 00:33:48,312
(Sky swing fee: 7 dollars)

1010
00:33:48,313 --> 00:33:49,712
Stop being so dramatic.

1011
00:33:49,713 --> 00:33:51,143
I wish we would stop going to high places.

1012
00:33:52,143 --> 00:33:53,583
It's scarier than I expected.

1013
00:33:54,083 --> 00:33:57,013
Really? If it makes you scared, it's impossible for us.

1014
00:33:57,253 --> 00:33:59,723
I'm brave, but I can't do it because of my weight.

1015
00:34:00,153 --> 00:34:01,352
Let's go, DinDin.

1016
00:34:01,353 --> 00:34:02,353
(Getting ready to go)

1017
00:34:02,353 --> 00:34:03,353
Goodbye.

1018
00:34:03,354 --> 00:34:04,463
(3 seconds before he's thrown to the sky)

1019
00:34:04,923 --> 00:34:06,023
(Making more fuss than the one actually riding it)

1020
00:34:06,393 --> 00:34:08,733
(Setting off towards the sky)

1021
00:34:08,933 --> 00:34:11,363
(DinDin soars smoothly.)

1022
00:34:11,733 --> 00:34:14,202
(A thrill so intense that it makes your eyes, nose, and mouth open)

1023
00:34:14,203 --> 00:34:15,303
I guess he's okay.

1024
00:34:15,703 --> 00:34:17,972
- Gosh, that looks amazing.
- He's coming back.

1025
00:34:17,973 --> 00:34:18,973
This is so...

1026
00:34:19,573 --> 00:34:22,673
(Dashing towards the sky through the refreshing wind)

1027
00:34:23,213 --> 00:34:24,213
(The moment when the blue sea and the sky meet)

1028
00:34:24,213 --> 00:34:25,213
My goodness.

1029
00:34:26,583 --> 00:34:29,113
- I'll let go of my hands.
- Go ahead.

1030
00:34:29,913 --> 00:34:32,382
(He spreads both arms to fully enjoy the wind from the sea.)

1031
00:34:32,383 --> 00:34:33,383
That's insane.

1032
00:34:34,423 --> 00:34:36,393
Thank you, Joon.

1033
00:34:36,893 --> 00:34:38,693
Seon Ho.

1034
00:34:39,893 --> 00:34:40,893
(He calls out the names of Team Fishing members.)

1035
00:34:40,894 --> 00:34:42,533
It's much more fun than I thought.

1036
00:34:44,663 --> 00:34:49,403
(At the same time, those whose names were called)

1037
00:34:49,533 --> 00:34:51,173
Are they really having fun?

1038
00:34:51,343 --> 00:34:52,373
Yes.

1039
00:34:52,803 --> 00:34:55,473
(The fishing inferno continues without a stop.)

1040
00:34:55,643 --> 00:34:59,243
(His complexion looks much worse due to the motion sickness.)

1041
00:34:59,313 --> 00:35:01,683
(Looking haggard)

1042
00:35:01,783 --> 00:35:02,783
Aren't you tired?

1043
00:35:03,013 --> 00:35:05,182
- It's because of seasickness.
- Is that why?

1044
00:35:05,183 --> 00:35:06,822
The boat is rocking so much.

1045
00:35:06,823 --> 00:35:07,823
(Waves that are stronger than expected)

1046
00:35:07,993 --> 00:35:11,063
I feel dizzy. I'm very seasick.

1047
00:35:11,563 --> 00:35:15,963
(Feeling awful from motion sickness that's getting worse)

1048
00:35:16,893 --> 00:35:18,903
(Dizzy)

1049
00:35:19,163 --> 00:35:20,833
You're doing well even though you're seasick.

1050
00:35:21,273 --> 00:35:23,433
I'm doing it with sheer willpower.

1051
00:35:24,033 --> 00:35:25,173
I feel very dizzy.

1052
00:35:25,743 --> 00:35:27,173
Let there be a big catch.

1053
00:35:27,403 --> 00:35:29,873
This feels like a workout.

1054
00:35:30,873 --> 00:35:31,913
We got some cuttlefish.

1055
00:35:32,783 --> 00:35:34,312
(They're happy to see cuttlefish.)

1056
00:35:34,313 --> 00:35:35,382
We caught two.

1057
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:37,483
- We got them.
- They're so big.

1058
00:35:39,453 --> 00:35:41,393
(Shooting out ink)

1059
00:35:43,993 --> 00:35:45,363
It got all over my clothes.

1060
00:35:45,993 --> 00:35:48,732
(Covered with ink)

1061
00:35:48,733 --> 00:35:50,193
Gosh, we caught two.

1062
00:35:50,693 --> 00:35:51,832
(The fishing of cuttlefish is going smoothly.)

1063
00:35:51,833 --> 00:35:53,033
- My gosh.
- It's a big one.

1064
00:35:53,333 --> 00:35:54,362
We got three.

1065
00:35:54,363 --> 00:35:56,573
(They caught three.)

1066
00:35:56,803 --> 00:35:58,373
We're getting a lot.

1067
00:35:59,873 --> 00:36:03,343
(The fishing is picking up speed.)

1068
00:36:06,343 --> 00:36:10,113
(Before they know it, they pile up a lot of cuttlefish.)

1069
00:36:11,923 --> 00:36:14,082
- You must be done.
- We're done.

1070
00:36:14,083 --> 00:36:15,452
Well done, everyone.

1071
00:36:15,453 --> 00:36:17,553
Good work. I wonder how many you caught.

1072
00:36:17,993 --> 00:36:19,763
They look like either 13 or 14 cuttlefish.

1073
00:36:20,263 --> 00:36:21,533
We caught a lot.

1074
00:36:22,933 --> 00:36:23,962
(Exclaiming)

1075
00:36:23,963 --> 00:36:25,563
(Flopping down)

1076
00:36:25,833 --> 00:36:28,402
(His legs go weak because of the persistent seasickness.)

1077
00:36:28,403 --> 00:36:29,503
I feel dizzy.

1078
00:36:30,503 --> 00:36:32,772
(Feeling terrible)

1079
00:36:32,773 --> 00:36:34,443
The work is very intense today.

1080
00:36:35,543 --> 00:36:37,783
I'm really dizzy. What do I do?

1081
00:36:38,783 --> 00:36:40,782
- Joon is seasick.
- Yes, I am.

1082
00:36:40,783 --> 00:36:42,283
This is no holiday.

1083
00:36:43,413 --> 00:36:45,722
Why am I the only one who's seasick?

1084
00:36:45,723 --> 00:36:46,922
Don't you feel seasick?

1085
00:36:46,923 --> 00:36:48,822
I must be cut out for working on a boat.

1086
00:36:48,823 --> 00:36:50,052
(Ironically, the person who dragged them here is totally fine.)

1087
00:36:50,053 --> 00:36:51,193
You know what?

1088
00:36:51,863 --> 00:36:54,123
Passion has nothing to do with it. Your body just collapses.

1089
00:36:54,193 --> 00:36:56,433
I feel like I had two bottles of soju.

1090
00:36:57,093 --> 00:36:58,532
(Woozy)

1091
00:36:58,533 --> 00:37:00,133
This is not a holiday.

1092
00:37:00,703 --> 00:37:02,203
Since you worked hard,

1093
00:37:02,473 --> 00:37:04,232
try some cuttlefish.

1094
00:37:04,233 --> 00:37:06,673
I'd love to. Joon is dying from seasickness.

1095
00:37:06,703 --> 00:37:09,243
I'd like to, but I can't eat.

1096
00:37:09,713 --> 00:37:10,812
(He cuts a fresh cuttlefish right on the spot.)

1097
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:11,912
It looks delicious.

1098
00:37:11,913 --> 00:37:13,543
- I should get ready to eat.
- Gosh.

1099
00:37:13,743 --> 00:37:16,052
Is it possible to try that on land?

1100
00:37:16,053 --> 00:37:17,452
(Despite his upset stomach, he's desperate to taste it.)

1101
00:37:17,453 --> 00:37:18,623
It looks delicious.

1102
00:37:18,753 --> 00:37:20,552
It's the freshest sashimi in the world.

1103
00:37:20,553 --> 00:37:21,553
(Plentiful and fresh)

1104
00:37:21,554 --> 00:37:23,752
It looks delicious. It must taste so good.

1105
00:37:23,753 --> 00:37:24,923
Hurry up and eat.

1106
00:37:25,193 --> 00:37:27,463
- Go ahead and try some.
- I would love to.

1107
00:37:27,623 --> 00:37:28,662
Thank you, sir.

1108
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:30,132
This is incredible.

1109
00:37:30,133 --> 00:37:33,933
(Dipping in a lot of chojang and taking a bite)

1110
00:37:35,573 --> 00:37:37,333
(Both eyes widening)

1111
00:37:37,603 --> 00:37:38,603
(Exclaiming)

1112
00:37:38,743 --> 00:37:39,872
What kind of texture is this?

1113
00:37:39,873 --> 00:37:40,873
(Surprised)

1114
00:37:40,873 --> 00:37:41,873
It's hard.

1115
00:37:42,043 --> 00:37:43,273
Don't eat it all.

1116
00:37:44,043 --> 00:37:45,243
I mean it.

1117
00:37:45,743 --> 00:37:48,652
(It tastes even better to eat it on the spot after fishing.)

1118
00:37:48,653 --> 00:37:50,053
Gosh, this is insane.

1119
00:37:50,153 --> 00:37:52,023
It's the best cuttlefish sashimi that I ever had.

1120
00:37:52,383 --> 00:37:54,792
I should try some too. After all, I caught them.

1121
00:37:54,793 --> 00:37:55,823
I'll leave you a few pieces.

1122
00:37:55,993 --> 00:37:57,392
It melts like sugar.

1123
00:37:57,393 --> 00:38:01,962
(A bite to staff members who also worked hard)

1124
00:38:01,963 --> 00:38:02,992
Isn't it insanely good?

1125
00:38:02,993 --> 00:38:04,662
I want to come here every day and eat them all.

1126
00:38:04,663 --> 00:38:05,702
(I would never get tired of them.)

1127
00:38:05,703 --> 00:38:07,563
This is romantic. Eating in the middle of the ocean.

1128
00:38:08,433 --> 00:38:09,502
It tastes excellent.

1129
00:38:09,503 --> 00:38:12,543
(As he's seasick, Joon is the only one who can't enjoy it.)

1130
00:38:13,273 --> 00:38:14,572
Leave me some.

1131
00:38:14,573 --> 00:38:15,573
(Eating with gluttony with one fewer person)

1132
00:38:15,574 --> 00:38:16,773
Don't finish it. I mean it.

1133
00:38:17,773 --> 00:38:18,942
It tastes so good.

1134
00:38:18,943 --> 00:38:21,013
It's so good that I'd like you to taste it.

1135
00:38:21,113 --> 00:38:22,153
Give me a piece.

1136
00:38:22,313 --> 00:38:23,413
- Really?
- Yes.

1137
00:38:25,783 --> 00:38:29,353
(In the end, he takes a bite.)

1138
00:38:29,793 --> 00:38:30,893
It's good.

1139
00:38:32,123 --> 00:38:33,393
It tastes really good.

1140
00:38:33,563 --> 00:38:34,633
Give me one more piece.

1141
00:38:34,993 --> 00:38:36,592
- Isn't it good?
- For now...

1142
00:38:36,593 --> 00:38:37,663
You can throw it up if you want.

1143
00:38:40,263 --> 00:38:41,432
- My gosh.
- Right?

1144
00:38:41,433 --> 00:38:42,672
(Impressed by the chewiness)

1145
00:38:42,673 --> 00:38:44,203
This is unbelievable.

1146
00:38:45,173 --> 00:38:47,003
If I can eat this despite feeling nauseous...

1147
00:38:47,673 --> 00:38:49,213
Let me have another one.

1148
00:38:49,873 --> 00:38:50,942
It's really good.

1149
00:38:50,943 --> 00:38:53,013
Why don't you just come here and eat?

1150
00:38:54,183 --> 00:38:56,253
Sitting on the edge could make you feel better.

1151
00:38:56,653 --> 00:38:58,352
I can't believe it. It tastes amazing.

1152
00:38:58,353 --> 00:38:59,822
(Grabbing with his bare hand)

1153
00:38:59,823 --> 00:39:01,853
(Eating)

1154
00:39:02,123 --> 00:39:03,823
Don't you feel better now that you ate?

1155
00:39:04,453 --> 00:39:05,893
I don't know, but I'm eating anyway.

1156
00:39:08,793 --> 00:39:10,132
Isn't it delicious?

1157
00:39:10,133 --> 00:39:12,262
(He feels completely recovered by the fresh taste.)

1158
00:39:12,263 --> 00:39:13,763
It tastes insanely good.

1159
00:39:13,863 --> 00:39:15,633
- It's too good to eat.
- Is there more?

1160
00:39:18,173 --> 00:39:19,842
I think you ate more than half.

1161
00:39:19,843 --> 00:39:21,272
(He eats well despite his upset stomach.)

1162
00:39:21,273 --> 00:39:23,243
I feel better after eating this.

1163
00:39:24,513 --> 00:39:26,113
It looks like I faked it.

1164
00:39:26,713 --> 00:39:27,782
How embarrassing.

1165
00:39:27,783 --> 00:39:30,482
I'm sick, but it tastes so good that I feel better.

1166
00:39:30,483 --> 00:39:32,923
We're going back to land.

1167
00:39:33,253 --> 00:39:35,892
You caught a total...

1168
00:39:35,893 --> 00:39:37,823
- of 13 cuttlefish.
- Okay.

1169
00:39:37,953 --> 00:39:40,292
Based on the market price,

1170
00:39:40,293 --> 00:39:42,933
- one is worth 12 dollars.
- That's all?

1171
00:39:42,993 --> 00:39:44,932
You caught a total of 13 cuttlefish,

1172
00:39:44,933 --> 00:39:46,262
but you ate one.

1173
00:39:46,263 --> 00:39:49,333
For 12 cuttlefish, you earned 144 dollars.

1174
00:39:49,373 --> 00:39:51,502
- That's how much you earned.
- And?

1175
00:39:51,503 --> 00:39:53,472
As you know, the other team is...

1176
00:39:53,473 --> 00:39:55,172
traveling on their own.

1177
00:39:55,173 --> 00:39:56,873
We're the only ones who have money.

1178
00:39:57,443 --> 00:40:00,782
Those who are traveling spent that money in advance.

1179
00:40:00,783 --> 00:40:02,012
(They spent it in advance.)

1180
00:40:02,013 --> 00:40:05,123
(The news finally hit them like a bolt from the blue.)

1181
00:40:05,483 --> 00:40:06,483
And so...

1182
00:40:06,823 --> 00:40:08,792
(Exploding with frustration)

1183
00:40:08,793 --> 00:40:10,252
That's so annoying.

1184
00:40:10,253 --> 00:40:12,693
They continue to spend money even now.

1185
00:40:12,763 --> 00:40:14,023
Are they out of their mind?

1186
00:40:14,933 --> 00:40:17,362
Here's a list of their expenses so far.

1187
00:40:17,363 --> 00:40:20,702
They spent 4.5 dollars on drinks, 84 dollars on electric bikes,

1188
00:40:20,703 --> 00:40:22,832
and 76 dollars at a cafeteria.

1189
00:40:22,833 --> 00:40:24,172
They rented a bicycle...

1190
00:40:24,173 --> 00:40:25,402
by paying 84 dollars?

1191
00:40:25,403 --> 00:40:27,502
- We don't have enough money.
- They really lost their mind.

1192
00:40:27,503 --> 00:40:29,342
How can you even spend 70 dollars at a cafeteria?

1193
00:40:29,343 --> 00:40:33,112
They spent 71.5 dollars on coffee and bread at a cafe,

1194
00:40:33,113 --> 00:40:35,052
six dollars to enter the skywalk,

1195
00:40:35,053 --> 00:40:37,583
and seven dollars for a ride on the sky swing.

1196
00:40:38,053 --> 00:40:39,952
As a result,

1197
00:40:39,953 --> 00:40:41,222
your pay balance is currently negative.

1198
00:40:41,223 --> 00:40:45,692
(Total allowance: Negative 105 dollars)

1199
00:40:45,693 --> 00:40:46,693
They've lost their mind.

1200
00:40:46,694 --> 00:40:49,162
In the end, you'll have to pay the debt.

1201
00:40:49,163 --> 00:40:50,262
Who will pay?

1202
00:40:50,263 --> 00:40:51,932
Then we just worked for free.

1203
00:40:51,933 --> 00:40:53,132
(They only got debt after working hard.)

1204
00:40:53,133 --> 00:40:54,262
I don't know about other items,

1205
00:40:54,263 --> 00:40:55,933
but renting expensive bikes was too much.

1206
00:40:56,173 --> 00:40:57,373
That's just crazy.

1207
00:40:57,973 --> 00:40:59,202
Goodness.

1208
00:40:59,203 --> 00:41:00,742
(They spent the value of 7 cuttlefish.)

1209
00:41:00,743 --> 00:41:03,013
Why would they ride bicycles here?

1210
00:41:03,173 --> 00:41:04,883
I lost all the motivation now.

1211
00:41:05,313 --> 00:41:06,742
It's only a start.

1212
00:41:06,743 --> 00:41:09,313
Who wants to start with a negative balance?

1213
00:41:10,413 --> 00:41:12,553
My goodness.

1214
00:41:12,723 --> 00:41:15,853
This is how you collapse while grabbing the back of your neck.

1215
00:41:16,693 --> 00:41:19,423
I worked really hard only for other people's sake.

1216
00:41:19,763 --> 00:41:21,022
Once I take a break,

1217
00:41:21,023 --> 00:41:22,893
I'll go and get beef. I'm serious.

1218
00:41:22,963 --> 00:41:24,492
I don't know who it is, but brace yourself.

1219
00:41:24,493 --> 00:41:25,702
I'm going to buy a convertible car.

1220
00:41:25,703 --> 00:41:28,502
- Today's trip is very pleasant.
- It's relaxing.

1221
00:41:28,503 --> 00:41:29,733
(Team Holiday arrives at the next mission spot.)

1222
00:41:29,933 --> 00:41:31,603
The color of the water is beautiful.

1223
00:41:32,603 --> 00:41:34,373
Why are we doing this again?

1224
00:41:35,043 --> 00:41:36,213
What's going on here?

1225
00:41:36,543 --> 00:41:38,142
This is their sick habit whenever we come to the sea.

1226
00:41:38,143 --> 00:41:40,043
Whenever we come to the sea...

1227
00:41:40,343 --> 00:41:43,382
Like dogs that leap into water as soon as they see it.

1228
00:41:43,383 --> 00:41:44,552
(To make it worse, the swim rings have numbers on them.)

1229
00:41:44,553 --> 00:41:46,353
They make us run into the water whenever we're at the sea.

1230
00:41:46,623 --> 00:41:47,823
Why do they keep doing this?

1231
00:41:47,983 --> 00:41:49,693
Some of them are disconnected.

1232
00:41:50,053 --> 00:41:52,362
Why are the three of us doing this? Things were going well.

1233
00:41:52,363 --> 00:41:53,422
(We were having a good time until now.)

1234
00:41:53,423 --> 00:41:54,792
Everyone, did you have a good time?

1235
00:41:54,793 --> 00:41:56,363
We weren't just having a good time.

1236
00:41:56,993 --> 00:41:59,002
We're talented at making footage.

1237
00:41:59,003 --> 00:42:01,262
- "Have a good time?"
- We weren't just having fun.

1238
00:42:01,263 --> 00:42:02,633
- How could you say that?
- We worked so hard.

1239
00:42:03,103 --> 00:42:04,133
I feel disappointed.

1240
00:42:04,303 --> 00:42:06,172
Weren't you enjoying your trip?

1241
00:42:06,173 --> 00:42:08,072
We were, but where are the other two?

1242
00:42:08,073 --> 00:42:09,973
- Are they still on the boat?
- They'll be here soon.

1243
00:42:10,043 --> 00:42:12,412
We brought them some bread.

1244
00:42:12,413 --> 00:42:14,212
- Just that one?
- "Just that one?"

1245
00:42:14,213 --> 00:42:15,413
What do you mean?

1246
00:42:15,483 --> 00:42:16,683
We also have coffee for them.

1247
00:42:17,013 --> 00:42:19,382
- Is he out of his mind?
- I've been trying very hard...

1248
00:42:19,383 --> 00:42:20,682
to save this coffee.

1249
00:42:20,683 --> 00:42:22,293
We also have some leftover scone.

1250
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:24,022
This is upsetting. Should we just finish it?

1251
00:42:24,023 --> 00:42:25,462
Gosh, let's just eat it.

1252
00:42:25,463 --> 00:42:27,463
- Say that we bought it like this.
- Okay.

1253
00:42:27,623 --> 00:42:29,493
They're coming from over there.

1254
00:42:29,733 --> 00:42:31,432
There's no energy in their walking, right?

1255
00:42:31,433 --> 00:42:33,403
- Where?
- What's going on over there?

1256
00:42:33,563 --> 00:42:35,232
- Goodness.
- What is it?

1257
00:42:35,233 --> 00:42:36,672
Look, there are swim rings again.

1258
00:42:36,673 --> 00:42:38,572
- We have to go in the water.
- Going in the water?

1259
00:42:38,573 --> 00:42:39,972
Are they crazy?

1260
00:42:39,973 --> 00:42:41,943
Why are things so terrible today?

1261
00:42:42,073 --> 00:42:43,843
They look very tired already.

1262
00:42:43,913 --> 00:42:45,242
But they ate cuttlefish.

1263
00:42:45,243 --> 00:42:46,343
Hurry up.

1264
00:42:46,543 --> 00:42:47,943
Walk. Don't hurry.

1265
00:42:48,143 --> 00:42:50,352
- They look quite upset.
- They look very upset.

1266
00:42:50,353 --> 00:42:51,353
(Looking gaunt already)

1267
00:42:51,354 --> 00:42:53,982
We heard some horrible news.

1268
00:42:53,983 --> 00:42:55,523
Seon Ho, you worked hard. Have some coffee.

1269
00:42:55,553 --> 00:42:57,652
Hold on. I don't care about your coffee.

1270
00:42:57,653 --> 00:43:00,492
We earned over 140 dollars by catching cuttlefish.

1271
00:43:00,493 --> 00:43:02,132
You spent 80 dollars on renting bicycles.

1272
00:43:02,133 --> 00:43:03,462
I did? No, I didn't.

1273
00:43:03,463 --> 00:43:06,562
We just earned 140 dollars, but we have a negative balance.

1274
00:43:06,563 --> 00:43:08,933
Don't you earn thousands of dollars from catching cuttlefish?

1275
00:43:09,573 --> 00:43:10,932
- What's wrong with you?
- It's cuttlefish.

1276
00:43:10,933 --> 00:43:11,972
- That's strange.
- I don't understand.

1277
00:43:11,973 --> 00:43:13,673
- That's what Joon told me.
- Come on!

1278
00:43:13,903 --> 00:43:16,342
I prepared a reward for you.

1279
00:43:16,343 --> 00:43:17,512
I'm starving.

1280
00:43:17,513 --> 00:43:19,513
- It's an amazing reward.
- Guess what it is.

1281
00:43:19,983 --> 00:43:21,852
- Some kind of candy?
- Croissant.

1282
00:43:21,853 --> 00:43:23,282
(Croissant)

1283
00:43:23,283 --> 00:43:24,882
We have something else for them.

1284
00:43:24,883 --> 00:43:26,752
- And...
- We have a different type.

1285
00:43:26,753 --> 00:43:28,353
- Here's a scone.
- Scone.

1286
00:43:28,523 --> 00:43:30,992
Oddly, this is how they make their scones.

1287
00:43:30,993 --> 00:43:32,493
I'm happy with this.

1288
00:43:33,123 --> 00:43:34,162
You don't want any, Joon?

1289
00:43:34,163 --> 00:43:35,432
(Grumbling)

1290
00:43:35,433 --> 00:43:36,493
I'll have some.

1291
00:43:36,633 --> 00:43:37,863
- This is all we have.
- That's okay.

1292
00:43:38,263 --> 00:43:39,463
What happened to your face?

1293
00:43:40,703 --> 00:43:41,872
(Ink sideburns)

1294
00:43:41,873 --> 00:43:43,632
- Sideburns?
- He broke out in a cold sweat.

1295
00:43:43,633 --> 00:43:45,872
- Really?
- Do cuttlefish spray ink that much?

1296
00:43:45,873 --> 00:43:46,873
Yes, they squirted a lot of ink.

1297
00:43:46,874 --> 00:43:48,272
- On this trip, - Yes.

1298
00:43:48,273 --> 00:43:50,312
it's all over if we get chosen to work. We must avoid it.

1299
00:43:50,313 --> 00:43:51,472
We're doomed when we're chosen.

1300
00:43:51,473 --> 00:43:53,212
- It was the worst. It was so hard.
- It was the worst.

1301
00:43:53,213 --> 00:43:54,213
Really?

1302
00:43:54,214 --> 00:43:55,453
That's not all. They said it was an easy job.

1303
00:43:55,513 --> 00:43:56,583
- Out of all the tasks today?
- Yes.

1304
00:43:56,853 --> 00:43:59,223
I got so seasick. It almost killed me.

1305
00:43:59,353 --> 00:44:01,893
Take your time and eat. We'll give you enough time for it.

1306
00:44:01,993 --> 00:44:04,963
Everyone, listen. This place we just got to is...

1307
00:44:05,423 --> 00:44:08,792
Songjeong Solbaram Beach, which features a beautiful forest...

1308
00:44:08,793 --> 00:44:10,932
filled with 100-year-old pine trees.

1309
00:44:10,933 --> 00:44:11,933
Songjeong Solbaram Beach?

1310
00:44:11,934 --> 00:44:13,133
- Yes.
- Songjeong Solbaram Beach?

1311
00:44:13,203 --> 00:44:15,132
What a gorgeous view! It makes me want to draw it.

1312
00:44:15,133 --> 00:44:16,173
Oh, my. Look over there.

1313
00:44:16,373 --> 00:44:18,233
The color is surreal.

1314
00:44:18,543 --> 00:44:20,673
I didn't know the Namhae Sea was this beautiful.

1315
00:44:20,773 --> 00:44:22,773
All right. Some of you...

1316
00:44:23,113 --> 00:44:24,312
- What?
- Again?

1317
00:44:24,313 --> 00:44:25,982
- I guess we're going somewhere.
- Some of you...

1318
00:44:25,983 --> 00:44:26,983
- What?
- Again?

1319
00:44:26,983 --> 00:44:27,983
- I guess we're going somewhere.
- Some of you will go right away...

1320
00:44:27,983 --> 00:44:28,983
(No way. That's not the case, right?)

1321
00:44:28,984 --> 00:44:31,453
The second fishing task of Working Holiday in Namhae is...

1322
00:44:32,323 --> 00:44:34,782
to catch the silver treasure of Namhae, the rich fishing ground.

1323
00:44:34,783 --> 00:44:36,422
- Anchovy. Is it jukbang anchovy?
- It must be anchovy.

1324
00:44:36,423 --> 00:44:39,663
You'll shake the nets to harvest anchovies, which are in season now.

1325
00:44:39,923 --> 00:44:41,893
Byung Man cried while doing that.

1326
00:44:42,363 --> 00:44:43,462
- Exactly.
- When he tried it,

1327
00:44:43,463 --> 00:44:44,563
he started crying while shaking the net.

1328
00:44:44,793 --> 00:44:46,203
He actually cried because it was so exhausting.

1329
00:44:47,303 --> 00:44:52,103
(Namhae anchovies are currently in season.)

1330
00:44:52,343 --> 00:44:54,642
(Some of the members must go out to the sea...)

1331
00:44:54,643 --> 00:44:57,473
(and earn money again.)

1332
00:44:57,773 --> 00:45:00,383
(Shaking anchovies off the nets is notorious for being exhausting.)

1333
00:45:00,483 --> 00:45:04,053
(Who will be chosen to do this task?)

1334
00:45:04,083 --> 00:45:06,152
Are we going out to sea on a boat?

1335
00:45:06,153 --> 00:45:08,692
- I'll explain to you.
- Isn't it jukbang anchovy?

1336
00:45:08,693 --> 00:45:11,322
2 Days 1 Night is famous for its random games.

1337
00:45:11,323 --> 00:45:12,522
(2 Days 1 Night is famous for its random games.)

1338
00:45:12,523 --> 00:45:14,463
You'll play Tube Diving Random Game to choose the members to work.

1339
00:45:15,863 --> 00:45:17,562
Each of you will pick a swim tube...

1340
00:45:17,563 --> 00:45:19,562
and run toward the sea.

1341
00:45:19,563 --> 00:45:22,702
I will hold onto three of them...

1342
00:45:22,703 --> 00:45:24,103
so you can't dive into the water.

1343
00:45:24,473 --> 00:45:26,972
Two of you who dive into the water...

1344
00:45:26,973 --> 00:45:28,342
will be exempt from the fishing task.

1345
00:45:28,343 --> 00:45:29,343
What?

1346
00:45:29,344 --> 00:45:30,873
- The two who dive into the water?
- Yes.

1347
00:45:31,243 --> 00:45:34,412
The three members who pick the tubes tied to the strings I'll hold...

1348
00:45:34,413 --> 00:45:35,452
will have to work.

1349
00:45:35,453 --> 00:45:36,783
- Three of us will work?
- Yes.

1350
00:45:36,813 --> 00:45:38,622
I've never wanted this badly to dive into the water.

1351
00:45:38,623 --> 00:45:40,022
- So from what I understand, - Exactly.

1352
00:45:40,023 --> 00:45:41,622
the two members who make it into the water will be exempt.

1353
00:45:41,623 --> 00:45:43,552
- That's correct.
- Team Holiday gets to shower...

1354
00:45:43,553 --> 00:45:44,692
and rest, lying in the room. Is that right?

1355
00:45:44,693 --> 00:45:47,463
The ones who dive will need to wash off.

1356
00:45:47,593 --> 00:45:48,792
Okay, everyone.

1357
00:45:48,793 --> 00:45:50,592
Please choose the tube number.

1358
00:45:50,593 --> 00:45:52,362
- Let's let them choose first.
- Let's do that.

1359
00:45:52,363 --> 00:45:54,662
- Absolutely.
- We're being considerate of you.

1360
00:45:54,663 --> 00:45:56,102
This is how much we care about you.

1361
00:45:56,103 --> 00:45:57,832
Seon Ho, I have a bad feeling about this for you.

1362
00:45:57,833 --> 00:45:59,273
I feel unlucky today for some reason.

1363
00:45:59,343 --> 00:46:01,002
I'll begin right away. I choose number three.

1364
00:46:01,003 --> 00:46:02,712
- No, we'll do it together.
- Just pick the number.

1365
00:46:02,713 --> 00:46:03,713
- Oh, that's it?
- Just pick the number for now.

1366
00:46:03,714 --> 00:46:04,742
I choose number three.

1367
00:46:04,743 --> 00:46:05,912
- Next up is Joon.
- It's Joon's turn now.

1368
00:46:05,913 --> 00:46:07,042
Choose your number.

1369
00:46:07,043 --> 00:46:08,182
I'll go with number two.

1370
00:46:08,183 --> 00:46:10,152
Joon picked number 2, and Seon Ho picked number 3.

1371
00:46:10,153 --> 00:46:12,682
(They desperately want to avoid fishing 2 times in a row.)

1372
00:46:12,683 --> 00:46:14,122
- I'll go with number 4.
- I'll go with number 5.

1373
00:46:14,123 --> 00:46:15,822
- Okay.
- Okay, then...

1374
00:46:15,823 --> 00:46:19,163
- One, two, three, four, and five.
- One, two, three, four, and five.

1375
00:46:19,663 --> 00:46:21,792
Does anyone want to switch numbers? Are you sticking with your choices?

1376
00:46:21,793 --> 00:46:23,462
- Yes.
- We wouldn't know, you know.

1377
00:46:23,463 --> 00:46:24,992
- We have no choice.
- You're right.

1378
00:46:24,993 --> 00:46:26,102
- I have a feeling...
- Shall we begin now?

1379
00:46:26,103 --> 00:46:28,163
I really didn't want to say this, but...

1380
00:46:28,433 --> 00:46:30,302
He just asked if any of us wanted to trade numbers.

1381
00:46:30,303 --> 00:46:31,303
(The psychological analyst of Director Joo is here.)

1382
00:46:31,304 --> 00:46:32,372
- These two.
- They must've chosen...

1383
00:46:32,373 --> 00:46:33,402
the wrong ones.

1384
00:46:33,403 --> 00:46:34,442
We'll give you a chance to trade numbers.

1385
00:46:34,443 --> 00:46:36,672
If you two are chosen, you'll be so exhausted.

1386
00:46:36,673 --> 00:46:38,142
For your information,

1387
00:46:38,143 --> 00:46:40,012
my thoughts may be obvious,

1388
00:46:40,013 --> 00:46:41,343
but I don't know which is which either.

1389
00:46:41,853 --> 00:46:43,382
- Sorry?
- I don't know which is which.

1390
00:46:43,383 --> 00:46:45,483
Are you left out even though you're the main director?

1391
00:46:45,923 --> 00:46:46,952
So, you're just sitting there as the director...

1392
00:46:46,953 --> 00:46:49,192
- without knowing which is which?
- That's right.

1393
00:46:49,193 --> 00:46:51,153
- He's basically a robot.
- This is hilarious.

1394
00:46:51,423 --> 00:46:53,163
A robot is not supposed to stutter like he does.

1395
00:46:53,793 --> 00:46:55,793
If you're going to be like this, why not just use an AI?

1396
00:46:56,463 --> 00:46:57,562
Are you sure you don't want to trade numbers?

1397
00:46:57,563 --> 00:46:59,362
- Do it while you can.
- I'll switch numbers with Se Yoon.

1398
00:46:59,363 --> 00:47:00,902
- I'm number 3.
- I'm number 4 now.

1399
00:47:00,903 --> 00:47:03,473
- I'll switch numbers with you.
- No. I don't want that.

1400
00:47:04,073 --> 00:47:05,702
- You want to switch?
- Okay.

1401
00:47:05,703 --> 00:47:06,772
- Good. Trade numbers.
- Let's trade numbers.

1402
00:47:06,773 --> 00:47:07,872
- Only Joon didn't switch.
- Are you sticking with your choice?

1403
00:47:07,873 --> 00:47:09,212
(Only Joon sticks with the number he chose before.)

1404
00:47:09,213 --> 00:47:10,213
I have a good feeling about this.

1405
00:47:10,214 --> 00:47:12,212
- You'll find out one at a time.
- I see.

1406
00:47:12,213 --> 00:47:14,912
We'll begin with Jong Min, who picked number one.

1407
00:47:14,913 --> 00:47:16,352
- Let's begin.
- Here we go.

1408
00:47:16,353 --> 00:47:17,553
Let's go.

1409
00:47:18,153 --> 00:47:19,323
I'll dive into the Namhae Sea.

1410
00:47:19,453 --> 00:47:21,022
- You shouldn't.
- I want to.

1411
00:47:21,023 --> 00:47:22,552
They need to rest.

1412
00:47:22,553 --> 00:47:24,823
- Go!
- To the Namhae Sea!

1413
00:47:25,263 --> 00:47:26,723
Here I go, off to meet anchovies!

1414
00:47:27,093 --> 00:47:29,263
- Wait, no.
- You don't want to meet anchovies.

1415
00:47:29,463 --> 00:47:30,662
That's what I picked earlier.

1416
00:47:30,663 --> 00:47:31,902
DinDin picked that before trading.

1417
00:47:31,903 --> 00:47:34,262
- Let's find out.
- Let's go to the Namhae Sea!

1418
00:47:34,263 --> 00:47:35,373
Please.

1419
00:47:35,703 --> 00:47:36,833
Gosh, I'm nervous.

1420
00:47:37,373 --> 00:47:39,142
Jong Min, can you hurry up?

1421
00:47:39,143 --> 00:47:40,202
Okay.

1422
00:47:40,203 --> 00:47:41,842
- Go, Jong Min!
- Go, Jong Min!

1423
00:47:41,843 --> 00:47:44,142
Let's go to Jeju Island. I'm going to Jeju Island.

1424
00:47:44,143 --> 00:47:45,182
(He just keeps shouting because he's nervous.)

1425
00:47:45,183 --> 00:47:47,443
- Let's go!
- Jong Min picked number one.

1426
00:47:48,013 --> 00:47:49,483
Jong Min is going to Jeju Island.

1427
00:47:49,613 --> 00:47:51,213
- Run cheerfully.
- Go!

1428
00:47:51,613 --> 00:47:53,052
Go now!

1429
00:47:53,053 --> 00:47:54,082
Let's go!

1430
00:47:54,083 --> 00:47:56,753
(He starts running!)

1431
00:48:00,263 --> 00:48:01,862
Let's go to the Namhae Sea!

1432
00:48:01,863 --> 00:48:03,563
(Fishing or diving)

1433
00:48:05,703 --> 00:48:08,363
(Falling down)

1434
00:48:09,503 --> 00:48:12,243
(Jong Min will go anchovy fishing.)

1435
00:48:12,403 --> 00:48:14,643
(Smiling from ear to ear)

1436
00:48:14,743 --> 00:48:16,943
This can't be. No!

1437
00:48:17,373 --> 00:48:20,083
- I have to go!
- Just a little further, Jong Min!

1438
00:48:20,283 --> 00:48:21,313
You can do it!

1439
00:48:21,643 --> 00:48:22,712
To the sea!

1440
00:48:22,713 --> 00:48:25,783
(He struggles with all his might, but the tube won't even budge.)

1441
00:48:25,953 --> 00:48:27,382
(Devastated)

1442
00:48:27,383 --> 00:48:28,482
- Nice.
- Nice.

1443
00:48:28,483 --> 00:48:31,692
- I picked number one earlier.
- Nice.

1444
00:48:31,693 --> 00:48:33,622
He traded luck with DinDin.

1445
00:48:33,623 --> 00:48:35,122
- Thank you.
- He looked like a baby turtle...

1446
00:48:35,123 --> 00:48:36,462
- crawling toward the sea.
- Go over there and play.

1447
00:48:36,463 --> 00:48:38,092
- Go ahead.
- Now we have a 25-percent chance.

1448
00:48:38,093 --> 00:48:40,063
- It's 50 percent.
- We have a 50-percent chance.

1449
00:48:40,363 --> 00:48:41,462
Good. Here we go.

1450
00:48:41,463 --> 00:48:42,672
You've got a better shot at resting now.

1451
00:48:42,673 --> 00:48:43,702
(Bitter)

1452
00:48:43,703 --> 00:48:45,202
Next up is Joon. I hope he gets picked.

1453
00:48:45,203 --> 00:48:47,742
If Joon gets picked, we'll have a 75-percent chance.

1454
00:48:47,743 --> 00:48:49,813
That won't happen. I'm going to dive into the water.

1455
00:48:50,713 --> 00:48:52,542
- Just wait and see.
- No sulking.

1456
00:48:52,543 --> 00:48:55,953
I won't... I have a good feeling. I'm practically psychic.

1457
00:48:56,513 --> 00:48:57,613
Watch me.

1458
00:48:57,883 --> 00:49:00,322
There's a pattern here. I figured it out.

1459
00:49:00,323 --> 00:49:02,122
- Really?
- There's a pattern, you know.

1460
00:49:02,123 --> 00:49:03,392
It makes a variety show more fun.

1461
00:49:03,393 --> 00:49:06,062
Fail, success, fail, success...

1462
00:49:06,063 --> 00:49:08,732
That's how the pattern goes.

1463
00:49:08,733 --> 00:49:10,363
The 1st 2 numbers should be the same.

1464
00:49:10,593 --> 00:49:12,002
I'll dive straight in.

1465
00:49:12,003 --> 00:49:13,003
(Will Joon be exempt from fishing just as he analyzed?)

1466
00:49:13,004 --> 00:49:14,603
- Here we go.
- Please fall backward.

1467
00:49:15,003 --> 00:49:16,672
- Please fail.
- Please let it be the wrong one.

1468
00:49:16,673 --> 00:49:17,873
- Please fail.
- Please.

1469
00:49:18,273 --> 00:49:20,603
2 Days 1 Night is hardcore!

1470
00:49:21,573 --> 00:49:23,612
(Please stop!)

1471
00:49:23,613 --> 00:49:25,212
- Please fail.
- Please fail.

1472
00:49:25,213 --> 00:49:27,217
(What could be the result?)

1473
00:49:27,218 --> 00:49:29,387
(Please stop!)

1474
00:49:29,388 --> 00:49:31,088
- Please fail.
- Please fail.

1475
00:49:32,158 --> 00:49:34,857
(He stops.)

1476
00:49:34,858 --> 00:49:36,087
Yes!

1477
00:49:36,088 --> 00:49:39,258
(Pattern, my foot.)

1478
00:49:41,198 --> 00:49:43,997
(Joon got picked for fishing 2 times in a row.)

1479
00:49:43,998 --> 00:49:45,067
I can't believe this. Darn it.

1480
00:49:45,068 --> 00:49:47,398
- Hey, come back here.
- Now we have a 75-percent chance.

1481
00:49:47,838 --> 00:49:49,038
We have a 75-percent chance.

1482
00:49:50,168 --> 00:49:52,577
- He's angry.
- No sulking.

1483
00:49:52,578 --> 00:49:53,837
- Joon is angry.
- It's over.

1484
00:49:53,838 --> 00:49:56,507
Hold on. I'm number three, so...

1485
00:49:56,508 --> 00:49:57,707
It's about time for a good one to come out.

1486
00:49:57,708 --> 00:49:59,447
It wouldn't make sense. If I failed,

1487
00:49:59,448 --> 00:50:01,077
both of the numbers 4 and 5 would succeed.

1488
00:50:01,078 --> 00:50:02,117
That wouldn't make sense.

1489
00:50:02,118 --> 00:50:04,288
- This is insane.
- I shouldn't have traded numbers.

1490
00:50:04,618 --> 00:50:05,618
I'm getting so excited.

1491
00:50:06,588 --> 00:50:07,588
(Sighing)

1492
00:50:10,058 --> 00:50:12,428
If Se Yoon fails, we'll automatically know the rest.

1493
00:50:12,598 --> 00:50:13,757
All right. It's Se Yoon's turn.

1494
00:50:13,758 --> 00:50:17,268
- I'm 100 percent sure about this.
- Fishing anchovies in Namhae...

1495
00:50:17,528 --> 00:50:19,198
is someone else's task!

1496
00:50:19,468 --> 00:50:21,568
It's not my problem! Let's go!

1497
00:50:21,838 --> 00:50:23,838
(Running with heavy footsteps)

1498
00:50:25,208 --> 00:50:27,338
(He keeps running without stopping!)

1499
00:50:27,578 --> 00:50:29,748
(Surprised)

1500
00:50:32,118 --> 00:50:33,978
(He dives straight in.)

1501
00:50:34,418 --> 00:50:37,688
(Diving has never felt this good before.)

1502
00:50:40,258 --> 00:50:41,657
(Se Yoon gets exempt from fishing 2 times in a row.)

1503
00:50:41,658 --> 00:50:42,988
I made it!

1504
00:50:44,728 --> 00:50:46,028
I made it!

1505
00:50:46,228 --> 00:50:48,198
I made it!

1506
00:50:48,498 --> 00:50:51,067
(Sullen)

1507
00:50:51,068 --> 00:50:52,898
I've never seen anyone who got so excited to dive in water.

1508
00:50:53,498 --> 00:50:56,307
(The remaining members feel like they're going crazy.)

1509
00:50:56,308 --> 00:50:57,438
My gosh.

1510
00:50:57,608 --> 00:51:00,638
(Se Yoon rubs it in with his celebratory dance.)

1511
00:51:01,748 --> 00:51:02,848
I can't believe this.

1512
00:51:04,078 --> 00:51:05,717
You have a 50-percent chance now.

1513
00:51:05,718 --> 00:51:06,877
It's either one of you.

1514
00:51:06,878 --> 00:51:08,048
Se Yoon, is the water cool?

1515
00:51:08,148 --> 00:51:09,418
Yes, it's cool.

1516
00:51:10,118 --> 00:51:11,147
It's cool.

1517
00:51:11,148 --> 00:51:12,688
I picked number three.

1518
00:51:13,058 --> 00:51:14,927
