Your business will fail if you run it like this.

2024
01:09:15,138 --> 01:09:16,667
- Will you only take 20 dollars?
- I'll pay 25 dollars.

2025
01:09:16,668 --> 01:09:17,838
- You'll pay 25 dollars? Okay.
- Yes.

2026
01:09:17,938 --> 01:09:20,877
You're a young man, but you can't do the math.

2027
01:09:20,878 --> 01:09:22,138
(He forgets about the members shaking anchovies.)

2028
01:09:22,908 --> 01:09:24,547
One, two. Let's go.

2029
01:09:24,548 --> 01:09:26,748
(They pay up and head back.)

2030
01:09:27,018 --> 01:09:29,848
If I become a regular, can you do the deliveries too?

2031
01:09:30,248 --> 01:09:32,388
- Fifty cents?
- Fifty cents. Of course.

2032
01:09:32,718 --> 01:09:34,158
One dollar.

2033
01:09:35,588 --> 01:09:37,128
We should go to the center.

2034
01:09:37,328 --> 01:09:38,627
- The center?
- The sun's not too hot.

2035
01:09:38,628 --> 01:09:39,628
Okay.

2036
01:09:39,629 --> 01:09:41,027
- This is yours.
- Okay.

2037
01:09:41,028 --> 01:09:42,328
We can set out the mat later. Take this.

2038
01:09:42,668 --> 01:09:45,067
Shall we lay it behind?

2039
01:09:45,068 --> 01:09:46,068
Okay.

2040
01:09:47,338 --> 01:09:48,737
It's perfect.

2041
01:09:48,738 --> 01:09:49,938
Nice.

2042
01:09:50,538 --> 01:09:52,237
(Shall we have some Chapagetti first?)

2043
01:09:52,238 --> 01:09:53,278
It looks amazing.

2044
01:09:54,038 --> 01:09:55,677
Smell that.

2045
01:09:55,678 --> 01:09:56,708
This is crazy.

2046
01:09:57,008 --> 01:09:58,108
The smell.

2047
01:09:58,378 --> 01:09:59,717
It's not cooked yet.

2048
01:09:59,718 --> 01:10:01,818
It's ready. Trust me. Do you trust me?

2049
01:10:02,448 --> 01:10:03,617
Try it.

2050
01:10:03,618 --> 01:10:04,987
- Me first?
- Try just a bit.

2051
01:10:04,988 --> 01:10:05,988
(He lets the younger brother have the precious first bite.)

2052
01:10:06,588 --> 01:10:08,787
Why did you switch from tongs to chopsticks?

2053
01:10:08,788 --> 01:10:09,888
(I won't decline the offer.)

2054
01:10:10,288 --> 01:10:12,928
(He fills his mouth with it.)

2055
01:10:13,058 --> 01:10:14,198
Is it ready? Are you sure?

2056
01:10:14,658 --> 01:10:16,668
- I told you. It's definitely ready.
- The tongs.

2057
01:10:17,698 --> 01:10:20,398
(Foodie Se Yoon also gets a large portion.)

2058
01:10:20,838 --> 01:10:22,397
(His mouth waters just from looking at it.)

2059
01:10:22,398 --> 01:10:23,537
It's really good.

2060
01:10:23,538 --> 01:10:24,538
(Gulping)

2061
01:10:24,908 --> 01:10:27,477
(He just eats from the bowl.)

2062
01:10:27,478 --> 01:10:28,478
Let me try this.

2063
01:10:28,778 --> 01:10:31,677
(He carefully blows on it.)

2064
01:10:31,678 --> 01:10:32,778
Is it good or not?

2065
01:10:34,148 --> 01:10:36,718
(This is what I'm talking about.)

2066
01:10:37,348 --> 01:10:41,858
(The noodles became even springier by the sea breeze.)

2067
01:10:42,018 --> 01:10:44,158
It tastes amazing.

2068
01:10:44,358 --> 01:10:45,628
- It's a delicacy.
- It's so good.

2069
01:10:46,228 --> 01:10:50,297
(They finish off every last noodle.)

2070
01:10:50,298 --> 01:10:51,327
It's great.

2071
01:10:51,328 --> 01:10:53,498
(They enjoy the very last bite.)

2072
01:10:54,198 --> 01:10:57,368
(His hat blows away in the strong wind.)

2073
01:10:57,968 --> 01:11:03,348
(Eating jjajang ramyeon while feeling the cool breeze)

2074
01:11:03,908 --> 01:11:07,517
(These two are also standing in the wind.)

2075
01:11:07,518 --> 01:11:10,748
(In denial)

2076
01:11:11,118 --> 01:11:14,518
(Their eyes are both fixed on the same spot.)

2077
01:11:14,758 --> 01:11:19,428
(Today's work site in the distance)

2078
01:11:19,958 --> 01:11:23,598
(The anchovies are being shaken off.)

2079
01:11:23,798 --> 01:11:26,028
(Moving in unison)

2080
01:11:27,068 --> 01:11:29,338
Only the real experts are there.

2081
01:11:30,538 --> 01:11:33,738
(Will we be able to do this well?)

2082
01:11:34,378 --> 01:11:35,378
I'll go.

2083
01:11:36,148 --> 01:11:37,347
Let's give it a try.

2084
01:11:37,348 --> 01:11:38,677
We can just give it a try and get out.

2085
01:11:38,678 --> 01:11:39,718
Let's go.

2086
01:11:39,978 --> 01:11:41,848
Let's go!

2087
01:11:42,148 --> 01:11:43,288
Goodness.

2088
01:11:43,818 --> 01:11:45,647
I've just been on boats all day today.

2089
01:11:45,648 --> 01:11:47,258
Is this "Workman?"

2090
01:11:47,818 --> 01:11:49,157
- Why is it so...
- It's "Workman" today.

2091
01:11:49,158 --> 01:11:50,657
- Working holiday.
- Right.

2092
01:11:50,658 --> 01:11:51,827
(It's Working Holiday, not Workman.)

2093
01:11:51,828 --> 01:11:53,198
Let's depart!

2094
01:11:53,298 --> 01:11:54,328
Nice.

2095
01:11:54,353 --> 01:11:56,615
(They head to the working holiday site.)

2096
01:11:56,640 --> 01:11:58,481
- We will sail off now!
- Gosh.

2097
01:11:58,482 --> 01:12:01,552
(They head to their working holiday spot.)

2098
01:12:01,822 --> 01:12:03,252
How are anchovies eaten?

2099
01:12:03,492 --> 01:12:05,052
How are they eaten?

2100
01:12:05,762 --> 01:12:08,462
You should earn the anchovies.

2101
01:12:08,522 --> 01:12:11,432
(We won't be able to have them?)

2102
01:12:11,532 --> 01:12:13,162
We didn't eat.

2103
01:12:13,702 --> 01:12:15,362
Do we not get lunch?

2104
01:12:16,302 --> 01:12:17,801
- We have to see how things go.
- What?

2105
01:12:17,802 --> 01:12:18,872
We have to see how things go.

2106
01:12:19,302 --> 01:12:22,142
We've been slacking. That must be why.

2107
01:12:23,172 --> 01:12:26,212
We might end up being called at 6pm the night before.

2108
01:12:27,942 --> 01:12:30,152
We might become UDT soldiers at this rate.

2109
01:12:31,712 --> 01:12:34,852
I heard you were preparing a 3 days and 2 nights special as well.

2110
01:12:35,152 --> 01:12:37,852
It was actually 3 days and 2 nights for you, Joon.

2111
01:12:38,022 --> 01:12:39,761
- Right.
- You departed at 11:30pm.

2112
01:12:39,762 --> 01:12:42,092
It was nice to spend 3 days and 2 nights.

2113
01:12:44,092 --> 01:12:45,092
Actually, it was tough.

2114
01:12:46,732 --> 01:12:48,502
You've been up...

2115
01:12:49,032 --> 01:12:51,602
for over 12 hours.

2116
01:12:52,072 --> 01:12:54,672
(No wonder he looked tired.)

2117
01:12:54,772 --> 01:12:55,772
Look over there.

2118
01:12:56,542 --> 01:12:57,841
They're all shaking it together.

2119
01:12:57,842 --> 01:12:59,981
That must be really tough to do.

2120
01:12:59,982 --> 01:13:02,411
There's a reason it's going to be tough.

2121
01:13:02,412 --> 01:13:03,851
Since we don't have the skills,

2122
01:13:03,852 --> 01:13:06,222
- we'll use so much strength.
- We'll be using our muscles.

2123
01:13:06,752 --> 01:13:08,721
- It's a dance move.
- There's a certain rhythm.

2124
01:13:08,722 --> 01:13:10,091
It's a dance move.

2125
01:13:10,092 --> 01:13:12,122
- One, two, three.
- It's like a dance challenge.

2126
01:13:12,462 --> 01:13:13,662
It's a dance move.

2127
01:13:14,492 --> 01:13:18,562
(Their moves are perfectly synced.)

2128
01:13:19,162 --> 01:13:20,832
That's fascinating.

2129
01:13:22,062 --> 01:13:24,571
There's a certain rhythm,

2130
01:13:24,572 --> 01:13:25,741
but we don't know it.

2131
01:13:25,742 --> 01:13:26,971
That's insane.

2132
01:13:26,972 --> 01:13:28,472
(Seeing it fills them up with worry.)

2133
01:13:28,942 --> 01:13:30,912
That's a muscle workout...

2134
01:13:31,442 --> 01:13:33,542
and cardio at the same time. It's death.

2135
01:13:34,182 --> 01:13:35,681
We should think it's a workout.

2136
01:13:35,682 --> 01:13:36,782
Right.

2137
01:13:37,152 --> 01:13:38,812
Byung Man cried.

2138
01:13:39,322 --> 01:13:41,482
Hiking must be better than this.

2139
01:13:42,052 --> 01:13:44,222
- They've been doing it nonstop.
- Right.

2140
01:13:44,352 --> 01:13:45,522
That's what's important.

2141
01:13:45,692 --> 01:13:47,892
The seagulls must be flying around for the anchovies.

2142
01:13:48,362 --> 01:13:50,332
- What?
- That must be why.

2143
01:13:50,562 --> 01:13:53,832
Are we supposed to be touched about that?

2144
01:13:54,132 --> 01:13:56,602
Are you telling us to enjoy the view or work?

2145
01:13:56,902 --> 01:13:57,932
A bit of both.

2146
01:13:58,302 --> 01:14:00,102
I think this will be very tough.

2147
01:14:00,842 --> 01:14:02,542
It will work out everything including our shoulders.

2148
01:14:02,942 --> 01:14:04,242
How is it done?

2149
01:14:04,312 --> 01:14:05,512
I'm not sure even after watching it.

2150
01:14:05,542 --> 01:14:08,312
We have to learn the choreography.

2151
01:14:08,882 --> 01:14:11,111
This is the workplace...

2152
01:14:11,112 --> 01:14:13,052
for the anchovy net-shaking.

2153
01:14:13,452 --> 01:14:16,422
(It's hard to predict how tough it will be.)

2154
01:14:16,792 --> 01:14:19,422
(Having mixed feelings)

2155
01:14:19,822 --> 01:14:22,222
Why does the net keep coming up without stopping?

2156
01:14:23,162 --> 01:14:24,961
They're moving their arms so quickly.

2157
01:14:24,962 --> 01:14:26,802
(It feels a lot more intense up close.)

2158
01:14:27,462 --> 01:14:30,131
(Is this something we can really pull off?)

2159
01:14:30,132 --> 01:14:31,402
It's a marvelous sight.

2160
01:14:33,042 --> 01:14:34,642
Let's get off first.

2161
01:14:35,172 --> 01:14:36,272
Let's go.

2162
01:14:36,972 --> 01:14:38,272
So hats must be worn.

2163
01:14:39,742 --> 01:14:43,712
(To block the anchovy scales flying all around,)

2164
01:14:43,982 --> 01:14:46,652
(a hat must be worn.)

2165
01:14:46,852 --> 01:14:47,852
I'll give it a try.

2166
01:14:47,853 --> 01:14:49,892
(Getting fully equipped)

2167
01:14:50,052 --> 01:14:53,122
After hearing from the captain, you two will start working.

2168
01:14:53,192 --> 01:14:55,661
This is the captain of the anchovy boat.

2169
01:14:55,662 --> 01:14:57,862
- Hello.
- Hello.

2170
01:14:57,992 --> 01:15:00,101
- Are Namhae anchovies famous?
- Yes.

2171
01:15:00,102 --> 01:15:01,701
Why are they famous?

2172
01:15:01,702 --> 01:15:05,002
This area is known for its clear waters.

2173
01:15:05,472 --> 01:15:07,172
The current is strong here...

2174
01:15:07,472 --> 01:15:11,472
and the anchovies here are of great quality.

2175
01:15:11,572 --> 01:15:15,382
What is the name of the anchovies we are catching today?

2176
01:15:15,812 --> 01:15:17,211
- The large anchovies.
- The large anchovies?

2177
01:15:17,212 --> 01:15:18,311
Right. The large anchovies.

2178
01:15:18,312 --> 01:15:19,982
- So they must be big.
- Right.

2179
01:15:20,052 --> 01:15:22,791
The work looks quite difficult.

2180
01:15:22,792 --> 01:15:24,752
- If we budge in, - It's quite tough.

2181
01:15:25,092 --> 01:15:26,691
wouldn't we be a hindrance?

2182
01:15:26,692 --> 01:15:29,462
There aren't as many anchovies today.

2183
01:15:29,592 --> 01:15:30,792
It won't be that tough today.

2184
01:15:30,832 --> 01:15:32,061
- I see.
- I see.

2185
01:15:32,062 --> 01:15:33,931
You chose the right day to come.

2186
01:15:33,932 --> 01:15:36,371
- Really? Okay.
- Really? That's a relief.

2187
01:15:36,372 --> 01:15:38,932
All you need is good teamwork.

2188
01:15:39,402 --> 01:15:42,811
You have to work well with the others.

2189
01:15:42,812 --> 01:15:46,742
But you don't seem to do this.

2190
01:15:47,842 --> 01:15:49,552
But you don't seem to do this.

2191
01:15:50,552 --> 01:15:52,211
Your hands look very pretty.

2192
01:15:52,212 --> 01:15:53,222
(Choking)

2193
01:15:53,422 --> 01:15:55,752
I did a lot of this in the past.

2194
01:15:55,892 --> 01:15:57,522
I'm too old now.

2195
01:15:58,122 --> 01:16:01,421
There will be someone who will teach you over there.

2196
01:16:01,422 --> 01:16:03,662
Head over there and learn how to do it.

2197
01:16:03,862 --> 01:16:05,031
- Thank you.
- Right.

2198
01:16:05,032 --> 01:16:06,401
Give it your best shot. Good luck!

2199
01:16:06,402 --> 01:16:07,801
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

2200
01:16:07,802 --> 01:16:09,162
(The two finally head over to the workplace.)

2201
01:16:09,402 --> 01:16:12,332
(Anchovy net-shaking)

2202
01:16:12,602 --> 01:16:13,771
(To prevent the freshly caught anchovies from getting spoiled,)

2203
01:16:13,772 --> 01:16:15,672
There seems to be a lot of them today.

2204
01:16:15,872 --> 01:16:18,772
(many of the anchovies caught on the net...)

2205
01:16:19,142 --> 01:16:21,641
(are shaken off with great strength...)

2206
01:16:21,642 --> 01:16:24,152
(to remove the scales and other foreign substances.)

2207
01:16:24,352 --> 01:16:25,952
- Hello.
- Hello.

2208
01:16:26,352 --> 01:16:28,822
(The two meet up with the veterans.)

2209
01:16:28,952 --> 01:16:31,192
(Oh Min Chul, supervisor)

2210
01:16:31,752 --> 01:16:34,021
(They start working right away.)

2211
01:16:34,022 --> 01:16:36,492
- Right hand, left hand.
- Together.

2212
01:16:37,332 --> 01:16:38,831
Right hand, left hand.

2213
01:16:38,832 --> 01:16:40,762
Right hand. One.

2214
01:16:43,172 --> 01:16:44,272
With a lot of strength.

2215
01:16:44,932 --> 01:16:46,172
Okay. Good.

2216
01:16:46,672 --> 01:16:48,841
(The work begins.)

2217
01:16:48,842 --> 01:16:50,971
One, two, three, four.

2218
01:16:50,972 --> 01:16:52,942
One, two, three, four.

2219
01:16:53,312 --> 01:16:56,651
(They try following the other workers.)

2220
01:16:56,652 --> 01:16:58,611
Do it together. Just like me.

2221
01:16:58,612 --> 01:16:59,822
I can't catch the net.

2222
01:17:01,052 --> 01:17:02,421
Just like me.

2223
01:17:02,422 --> 01:17:03,592
- Hold on.
- One, two.

2224
01:17:03,822 --> 01:17:04,992
Hold on.

2225
01:17:05,022 --> 01:17:07,092
Come this way.

2226
01:17:07,892 --> 01:17:09,191
- One, two.
- One, two.

2227
01:17:09,192 --> 01:17:11,032
- One, two.
- Stay still.

2228
01:17:11,232 --> 01:17:14,032
(The key point is to pull the net in sync.)

2229
01:17:14,462 --> 01:17:15,631
I keep missing the net.

2230
01:17:15,632 --> 01:17:17,901
Grab the net.

2231
01:17:17,902 --> 01:17:19,772
- Grab the net.
- Right.

2232
01:17:21,842 --> 01:17:25,542
(They're eager to work hard, but it's hard to do.)

2233
01:17:26,282 --> 01:17:28,742
- It's too hard.
- One, two, three, four.

2234
01:17:29,242 --> 01:17:31,852
(They try their best to follow along.)

2235
01:17:36,492 --> 01:17:39,792
(The net keeps getting missed.)

2236
01:17:39,992 --> 01:17:41,792
(Checking)

2237
01:17:42,062 --> 01:17:44,662
(Fortunately, he didn't notice it.)

2238
01:17:45,592 --> 01:17:49,372
(They start singing the work song to bring up the atmosphere.)

2239
01:17:49,972 --> 01:17:55,672
(Let's shake it!)

2240
01:17:55,702 --> 01:17:57,511
(Let's shake it!)

2241
01:17:57,512 --> 01:17:59,441
(Let's shake it!)

2242
01:17:59,442 --> 01:18:01,142
Gosh!

2243
01:18:01,312 --> 01:18:02,482
Let's shake it!

2244
01:18:03,482 --> 01:18:07,222
(His glove is causing trouble this time.)

2245
01:18:07,422 --> 01:18:08,451
I'm sorry!

2246
01:18:08,452 --> 01:18:09,591
Hurry!

2247
01:18:09,592 --> 01:18:11,521
- Let's shake it.
- Hurry!

2248
01:18:11,522 --> 01:18:14,162
(Meanwhile, Joon seems to have gotten the hang of it.)

2249
01:18:14,692 --> 01:18:17,831
(Full of passion)

2250
01:18:17,832 --> 01:18:20,531
- Let's shake it!
- Hey!

2251
01:18:20,532 --> 01:18:22,832
(Joon's camera)

2252
01:18:23,072 --> 01:18:24,371
- Hey!
- What's wrong?

2253
01:18:24,372 --> 01:18:25,801
(His glove is causing trouble as well.)

2254
01:18:25,802 --> 01:18:27,772
- Are there more gloves?
- The gloves are...

2255
01:18:28,572 --> 01:18:31,142
- They keep coming off.
- Pass the cotton gloves. Gosh.

2256
01:18:31,272 --> 01:18:32,272
I want new gloves as well.

2257
01:18:32,273 --> 01:18:34,442
(I want new gloves as well.)

2258
01:18:34,942 --> 01:18:38,152
(They quickly switch their gloves.)

2259
01:18:38,612 --> 01:18:40,121
Do it just like me.

2260
01:18:40,122 --> 01:18:41,881
- Right.
- Do it just like me.

2261
01:18:41,882 --> 01:18:42,921
Just like you.

2262
01:18:42,922 --> 01:18:44,622
- Just like me.
- Exactly like him.

2263
01:18:45,092 --> 01:18:46,362
Get ready.

2264
01:18:46,692 --> 01:18:47,692
Start.

2265
01:18:47,693 --> 01:18:49,391
- One, two.
- One, two! Heave-ho!

2266
01:18:49,392 --> 01:18:51,292
(When the supervisor starts the chant,)

2267
01:18:51,362 --> 01:18:53,302
One, two! Let's hit it!

2268
01:18:54,132 --> 01:18:56,872
(they follow the rhythm.)

2269
01:18:56,932 --> 01:18:58,772
- One, two! Let's shake it!
- Let's shake it!

2270
01:18:59,002 --> 01:19:01,342
(They start following the rhythm with the work song.)

2271
01:19:01,642 --> 01:19:04,442
(The anchovy net-shaking starts in earnest.)

2272
01:19:05,372 --> 01:19:08,982
(As they follow along,)

2273
01:19:09,212 --> 01:19:12,412
(the two start to get adjusted to the workplace.)

2274
01:19:12,782 --> 01:19:15,051
(A battle of pride...)

2275
01:19:15,052 --> 01:19:18,622
(of anchovies and humans)

2276
01:19:19,492 --> 01:19:20,492
We're good, aren't we?

2277
01:19:20,493 --> 01:19:22,221
- Let's hit it! One, two!
- One, two!

2278
01:19:22,222 --> 01:19:23,791
- Let's hit it! One, two!
- One, two!

2279
01:19:23,792 --> 01:19:26,362
(He's doing pretty well.)

2280
01:19:26,402 --> 01:19:28,061
- One, two!
- One, two! Heoya, choya!

2281
01:19:28,062 --> 01:19:30,002
- Heoya, choi!
- Heoya, heoyi!

2282
01:19:30,372 --> 01:19:33,072
(They start to speed up.)

2283
01:19:33,342 --> 01:19:35,142
- Gosh!
- Why is it so fast?

2284
01:19:35,842 --> 01:19:38,412
(They start to speed up more and more.)

2285
01:19:38,712 --> 01:19:40,341
- One, two!
- Heoya, choya!

2286
01:19:40,342 --> 01:19:42,141
- One, two!
- Heoya, choya!

2287
01:19:42,142 --> 01:19:45,582
(The anchovy net-shaking gets more intense.)

2288
01:19:46,552 --> 01:19:48,451
(The faster work speed...)

2289
01:19:48,452 --> 01:19:51,352
(makes him falter.)

2290
01:19:53,462 --> 01:19:54,622
I lost my balance.

2291
01:19:55,822 --> 01:19:58,392
Let's shake it! Gosh, I'm falling back!

2292
01:19:58,932 --> 01:20:00,802
Let's shake it!

2293
01:20:01,032 --> 01:20:03,001
(He loses his position...)

2294
01:20:03,002 --> 01:20:05,772
(and returns.)

2295
01:20:06,242 --> 01:20:09,102
(They're finally experiencing the pace of work.)

2296
01:20:10,512 --> 01:20:13,512
(He opens up his hood as the work got faster.)

2297
01:20:13,982 --> 01:20:16,981
(Work mode on)

2298
01:20:16,982 --> 01:20:19,251
- Gosh, this is exhausting!
- Heoya, choya!

2299
01:20:19,252 --> 01:20:20,951
- Hey!
- Go!

2300
01:20:20,952 --> 01:20:22,821
- Hey!
- There you go!

2301
01:20:22,822 --> 01:20:25,321
- Let's go!
- Good job!

2302
01:20:25,322 --> 01:20:27,022
(He carries on even when his hat came off.)

2303
01:20:28,092 --> 01:20:31,262
(Without caring about the anchovies falling over them,)

2304
01:20:32,162 --> 01:20:37,802
(they carry on with the battle against the anchovies.)

2305
01:20:38,432 --> 01:20:40,871
(Only their heavy breathing can be heard.)

2306
01:20:40,872 --> 01:20:43,272
- Our hands aren't in sync.
- Let's shake it!

2307
01:20:43,542 --> 01:20:45,111
- Let's shake it!
- Our hands aren't in sync!

2308
01:20:45,112 --> 01:20:46,112
It's a mess.

2309
01:20:46,113 --> 01:20:47,711
- Heoya, choya!
- Heoya, choya!

2310
01:20:47,712 --> 01:20:51,782
(Don't fall behind.)

2311
01:20:52,452 --> 01:20:55,422
(As they carry on with the tough work,)

2312
01:20:55,622 --> 01:20:56,691
(the two start to get exhausted.)

2313
01:20:56,692 --> 01:20:58,351
- Get in sync!
- Let's shake it!

2314
01:20:58,352 --> 01:21:00,262
- Get in sync!
- Get in sync!

2315
01:21:00,822 --> 01:21:05,462
(Around 30 minutes have passed.)

2316
01:21:07,032 --> 01:21:08,831
(Around 30 seconds have passed since they started boiling the water.)

2317
01:21:08,832 --> 01:21:09,931
- Right.
- Right.

2318
01:21:09,932 --> 01:21:12,072
(Peaceful)

2319
01:21:12,202 --> 01:21:14,342
(Turning back)

2320
01:21:14,472 --> 01:21:16,771
Is someone here? Who is it?

2321
01:21:16,772 --> 01:21:18,741
He must've made it back alive.

2322
01:21:18,742 --> 01:21:19,812
Awesome!

2323
01:21:19,942 --> 01:21:21,041
- Guys!
- Are you serious?

2324
01:21:21,042 --> 01:21:22,242
(Jong Min made it back alive.)

2325
01:21:22,382 --> 01:21:23,552
I'm back alive!

2326
01:21:23,712 --> 01:21:24,752
Gosh.

2327
01:21:25,912 --> 01:21:27,181
I'm back alive!

2328
01:21:27,182 --> 01:21:28,222
(The whole universe backs the appearance of Jong Min.)

2329
01:21:28,282 --> 01:21:29,792
Is this an extra scene? What is going on?

2330
01:21:30,852 --> 01:21:32,151
- Why are you here?
- Why are you here?

2331
01:21:32,152 --> 01:21:33,162
You two are here?

2332
01:21:34,262 --> 01:21:35,692
- How did you get here?
- Let's eat!

2333
01:21:35,892 --> 01:21:36,892
- Jong Min!
- Jong Min.

2334
01:21:36,893 --> 01:21:38,231
There are still five packets of ramyeon.

2335
01:21:38,232 --> 01:21:39,602
What? How many did you have?

2336
01:21:40,132 --> 01:21:41,631
Come to the center and tell us what happened.

2337
01:21:41,632 --> 01:21:44,002
- Me?
- How did you end up here?

2338
01:21:44,132 --> 01:21:45,832
Me? The thing is...

2339
01:21:46,642 --> 01:21:47,841
I know how hard anchovy fishing is.

2340
01:21:47,842 --> 01:21:48,871
Right.

2341
01:21:48,872 --> 01:21:50,271
(I played a card game with Joon and DinDin.)

2342
01:21:50,272 --> 01:21:51,411
(It seemed like DinDin would win, but he lost first.)

2343
01:21:51,412 --> 01:21:52,671
(And during the game with Joon, he lost his concentration,)

2344
01:21:52,672 --> 01:21:53,812
(so I ended up winning.)

2345
01:21:54,782 --> 01:21:56,182
Unbelievable.

2346
01:21:56,552 --> 01:21:58,552
Then, did you get here with your skill, not luck?

2347
01:21:58,752 --> 01:22:00,822
My skill... Actually, this is my first time.

2348
01:22:01,882 --> 01:22:03,722
I won with my skill for the first time.

2349
01:22:04,352 --> 01:22:06,722
We should have a welcome ceremony.

2350
01:22:07,092 --> 01:22:08,991
- Welcome back.
- The medal will be awarded.

2351
01:22:08,992 --> 01:22:10,191
(Congratulations on joining our camping trip.)

2352
01:22:10,192 --> 01:22:11,332
Congratulations.

2353
01:22:12,192 --> 01:22:13,431
Is this all there is to eat?

2354
01:22:13,432 --> 01:22:14,561
- Jong Min.
- Yes?

2355
01:22:14,562 --> 01:22:15,562
(Looking around)

2356
01:22:15,632 --> 01:22:17,532
You have to bring your own camping chair.

2357
01:22:18,072 --> 01:22:19,971
- You have to pay to buy a chair.
- You have to pay.

2358
01:22:19,972 --> 01:22:21,371
- Really?
- You have to buy one.

2359
01:22:21,372 --> 01:22:22,941
Just buy one for now.

2360
01:22:22,942 --> 01:22:23,942
No.

2361
01:22:24,372 --> 01:22:29,882
(They promised earlier not to spend money.)

2362
01:22:30,012 --> 01:22:31,682
I wasn't going to watch my spending,

2363
01:22:32,152 --> 01:22:33,851
- but after seeing the members go, - You felt bad for them?

2364
01:22:33,852 --> 01:22:35,622
- I couldn't spend money.
- How do you really feel?

2365
01:22:36,792 --> 01:22:37,792
I want to eat.

2366
01:22:37,793 --> 01:22:38,892
(Laughing)

2367
01:22:39,192 --> 01:22:40,391
Let's just eat what we have.

2368
01:22:40,392 --> 01:22:41,861
- Let's eat all together.
- Let's eat.

2369
01:22:41,862 --> 01:22:43,332
Just get him a chair.

2370
01:22:43,492 --> 01:22:44,992
It's okay if you don't eat.

2371
01:22:45,132 --> 01:22:46,402
No. I'm going to eat.

2372
01:22:46,532 --> 01:22:48,002
But I'll just eat what you have.

2373
01:22:48,302 --> 01:22:49,771
(They open the lid to see if it's well cooked.)

2374
01:22:49,772 --> 01:22:50,772
It's done.

2375
01:22:50,773 --> 01:22:52,301
- No. Not yet.
- It's done.

2376
01:22:52,302 --> 01:22:53,541
It's too firm yet.

2377
01:22:53,542 --> 01:22:54,672
I like firm noodles.

2378
01:22:55,942 --> 01:22:57,812
Go ahead and eat.

2379
01:22:58,172 --> 01:23:00,111
- Well done, Jong Min.
- I really wanted to eat.

2380
01:23:00,112 --> 01:23:01,382
- Let me do it for you.
- Use the ladle.

2381
01:23:01,682 --> 01:23:02,952
Who would eat Neoguri like this?

2382
01:23:03,512 --> 01:23:04,781
It's like shabu-shabu.

2383
01:23:04,782 --> 01:23:05,812
It's okay.

2384
01:23:07,052 --> 01:23:09,752
Still, this is a camping trip. Have some broth.

2385
01:23:09,792 --> 01:23:11,392
Gosh, the broth is amazing.

2386
01:23:11,752 --> 01:23:13,022
It's so chewy.

2387
01:23:13,362 --> 01:23:14,391
It's not cooked at all.

2388
01:23:14,392 --> 01:23:15,492
(Laughing)

2389
01:23:16,862 --> 01:23:19,332
- See? I told you.
- My gosh, this is...

2390
01:23:20,732 --> 01:23:22,001
(Choking)

2391
01:23:22,002 --> 01:23:23,802
- How is it?
- It's like jjolmyeon.

2392
01:23:25,172 --> 01:23:26,342
It's too firm, Jong Min.

2393
01:23:26,502 --> 01:23:27,502
I know.

2394
01:23:27,602 --> 01:23:29,602
- But it tastes good.
- It's good when eaten together.

2395
01:23:29,812 --> 01:23:31,271
- You even eat raw noodles, right?
- Sure.

2396
01:23:31,272 --> 01:23:32,342
(It tastes good anyway.)

2397
01:23:33,182 --> 01:23:36,982
(There's no way ramyeon eaten outside tastes bad.)

2398
01:23:37,112 --> 01:23:38,651
You and I are so lucky.

2399
01:23:38,652 --> 01:23:39,652
Right. So far.

2400
01:23:40,582 --> 01:23:43,422
My cameraman said I looked the coolest he's ever seen me.

2401
01:23:43,922 --> 01:23:45,121
- He did?
- He didn't know I was like that.

2402
01:23:45,122 --> 01:23:46,252
- After watching you play the game?
- Yes.

2403
01:23:46,522 --> 01:23:48,122
If I lost, he'd have to go with me.

2404
01:23:48,692 --> 01:23:50,762
- He returned alive thanks to you.
- Right.

2405
01:23:51,232 --> 01:23:52,461
Let's not try to be nice people.

2406
01:23:52,462 --> 01:23:53,701
- Let's do that.
- Okay?

2407
01:23:53,702 --> 01:23:55,632
We're already here. How can we be nice?

2408
01:23:55,902 --> 01:23:57,202
But that doesn't mean we're bad people.

2409
01:23:57,432 --> 01:23:58,672
No.

2410
01:23:58,872 --> 01:24:01,242
(We're just full.)

2411
01:24:03,212 --> 01:24:05,911
(Now that their stomach is full,)

2412
01:24:05,912 --> 01:24:07,042
(they appreciate a moment of peace.)

2413
01:24:09,412 --> 01:24:12,682
(A beach with a cool breeze and delicious food)

2414
01:24:13,452 --> 01:24:17,452
(At the same time, on another sea)

2415
01:24:17,892 --> 01:24:20,792
(They're still busy harvesting anchovies.)

2416
01:24:21,792 --> 01:24:25,732
(The unending war with the anchovies)

2417
01:24:26,602 --> 01:24:29,772
(Exhausted to the bone from the grueling, repetitive labor)

2418
01:24:30,132 --> 01:24:33,842
(As their consciousness fades away,)

2419
01:24:34,372 --> 01:24:37,272
(the only thing they can see before their eyes...)

2420
01:24:38,042 --> 01:24:41,612
(is a flurry of anchovy scales.)

2421
01:24:42,282 --> 01:24:45,782
(Anchovy scales falling like snow)

2422
01:24:46,352 --> 01:24:50,392
(Team Fishing working hard under the scorching sun)

2423
01:24:51,292 --> 01:24:53,862
(I wonder if Jong Min is happy.)

2424
01:24:54,122 --> 01:24:56,692
(That's right.)

2425
01:24:56,832 --> 01:25:00,062
(The workplace is filled only with the echoes of a hollow work song.)

2426
01:25:00,432 --> 01:25:02,332
(Still, what’s started must be finished.)

2427
01:25:02,432 --> 01:25:04,372
(We can't give up here.)

2428
01:25:04,632 --> 01:25:06,872
(Under the captain's command,)

2429
01:25:07,072 --> 01:25:09,602
(everyone shakes off the anchovies in perfect unison.)

2430
01:25:10,072 --> 01:25:12,742
(This is like...)

2431
01:25:15,512 --> 01:25:18,852
(An orchestra of labor?)

2432
01:25:21,182 --> 01:25:25,192
(Silvery fragments scattering into their mouth)

2433
01:25:26,322 --> 01:25:27,362
(Just give me one bite.)

2434
01:25:28,692 --> 01:25:31,392
(An endless war with the anchovies)

2435
01:25:32,992 --> 01:25:34,732
- Heave-ho.
- Heave-ho.

2436
01:25:34,802 --> 01:25:39,102
(One team is engaged in extreme work of shaking off anchovies.)

2437
01:25:39,902 --> 01:25:42,872
(At that exact moment)

2438
01:25:44,242 --> 01:25:47,382
(The other is enjoying sweet, blissful rest.)

2439
01:25:49,782 --> 01:25:51,512
We should lay out a mat and take a nap.

2440
01:25:51,882 --> 01:25:54,922
(The Working Holiday of absolute extremes)

2441
01:25:55,552 --> 01:25:58,392
(The heavy labor continues.)

2442
01:25:58,752 --> 01:26:00,392
(An endless swarm of anchovies rushing in)

2443
01:26:00,762 --> 01:26:04,161
(Facing them head-on without backing down)

2444
01:26:04,162 --> 01:26:06,902
(But thanks to their noticeably faster hands,)

2445
01:26:07,232 --> 01:26:10,772
(the grueling work gets a little easier.)

2446
01:26:11,202 --> 01:26:15,302
(Becoming one with the anchovies)

2447
01:26:16,002 --> 01:26:20,142
(They're pretty good at this now.)

2448
01:26:20,742 --> 01:26:22,781
(The highest-difficulty task in 2 Days 1 Night history)

2449
01:26:22,782 --> 01:26:24,952
(Anchovy fishing)

2450
01:26:25,212 --> 01:26:27,422
Okay. The last one. We're almost done.

2451
01:26:28,882 --> 01:26:30,692
- We're almost done.
- We're almost done.

2452
01:26:31,792 --> 01:26:35,192
(They summon their remaining strength for the last net.)

2453
01:26:35,822 --> 01:26:36,962
Okay!

2454
01:26:38,032 --> 01:26:40,432
(No anchovies are seen on the net.)

2455
01:26:40,962 --> 01:26:42,131
We're done!

2456
01:26:42,132 --> 01:26:43,232
(The work is finished after 1 hour of shaking.)

2457
01:26:43,372 --> 01:26:44,872
- Great work, guys.
- Good work.

2458
01:26:45,902 --> 01:26:47,002
Well done.

2459
01:26:47,842 --> 01:26:48,941
(Tapping)

2460
01:26:48,942 --> 01:26:49,942
Good work.

2461
01:26:50,342 --> 01:26:51,342
Great.

2462
01:26:51,343 --> 01:26:53,882
(He's so cool.)

2463
01:26:54,512 --> 01:26:56,111
(After the work, all the strength drained out from their legs.)

2464
01:26:56,112 --> 01:26:57,311
We're done.

2465
01:26:57,312 --> 01:26:58,882
(After the work, all the strength drained out from their legs.)

2466
01:26:59,182 --> 01:27:03,252
(They gave it their all.)

2467
01:27:03,352 --> 01:27:06,452
(Wiped out)

2468
01:27:06,892 --> 01:27:11,162
(They finally have a sip of water.)

2469
01:27:19,572 --> 01:27:20,942
This is such an extreme work.

2470
01:27:21,442 --> 01:27:23,442
This is a job that not just anyone can do.

2471
01:27:23,972 --> 01:27:25,571
- This is...
- It's the hardest thing I've done.

2472
01:27:25,572 --> 01:27:27,642
- It was driving you nuts, right?
-Yes.

2473
01:27:28,482 --> 01:27:30,712
I had to control my mind every single time.

2474
01:27:30,952 --> 01:27:32,382
"I can't give up here."

2475
01:27:32,612 --> 01:27:35,322
The strength drained out from my arms completely.

2476
01:27:36,122 --> 01:27:38,922
I just kept thinking, "I can't give up here."

2477
01:27:41,292 --> 01:27:43,761
If I give up, it will make things harder for the others.

2478
01:27:43,762 --> 01:27:44,762
Exactly.

2479
01:27:45,662 --> 01:27:46,732
My goodness.

2480
01:27:48,502 --> 01:27:49,531
(The lingering aftertaste of the anchovies wouldn't fade.)

2481
01:27:49,532 --> 01:27:50,902
It's much harder than it looks.

2482
01:27:51,532 --> 01:27:53,201
And they do this for four hours?

2483
01:27:53,202 --> 01:27:55,441
That's impossible. That's just...

2484
01:27:55,442 --> 01:27:56,501
(Unbelievable)

2485
01:27:56,502 --> 01:27:59,412
This is the hardest work ever.

2486
01:27:59,742 --> 01:28:03,511
Just thinking about doing this for four hours makes me want to cry.

2487
01:28:03,512 --> 01:28:04,982
I want to go home.

2488
01:28:05,252 --> 01:28:07,552
All right, everyone. I'll give you a short break.

2489
01:28:09,252 --> 01:28:10,521
(A short break?)

2490
01:28:10,522 --> 01:28:11,522
What?

2491
01:28:12,292 --> 01:28:13,761
- Darn it.
- Don't be like that.

2492
01:28:13,762 --> 01:28:14,962
What are you talking about?

2493
01:28:15,122 --> 01:28:17,262
Seriously, stop it. What are we going to do?

2494
01:28:18,692 --> 01:28:21,001
A boat is coming to pick us up.

2495
01:28:21,002 --> 01:28:22,731
You can take a break until then.

2496
01:28:22,732 --> 01:28:24,371
(An unbelievable reality)

2497
01:28:24,372 --> 01:28:25,432
Have a seat.

2498
01:28:27,872 --> 01:28:31,072
What's all this? We've been on a boat since 7am.

2499
01:28:31,612 --> 01:28:34,041
And I threw up when I got here.

2500
01:28:34,042 --> 01:28:35,981
(He has no energy to argue.)

2501
01:28:35,982 --> 01:28:38,012
- My goodness.
- Is anchovy fishing...

2502
01:28:38,382 --> 01:28:40,951
the hardest job on the sea?

2503
01:28:40,952 --> 01:28:42,321
You can say that.

2504
01:28:42,322 --> 01:28:44,692
I think this job is overwhelmingly grueling.

2505
01:28:45,052 --> 01:28:48,162
This isn't about working time. I can't do this even for an hour.

2506
01:28:48,692 --> 01:28:49,721
You just can't do it.

2507
01:28:49,722 --> 01:28:51,632
(In the meantime, a boat heading to the dock arrives.)

2508
01:28:53,332 --> 01:28:55,831
Get on the boat and take a seat.

2509
01:28:55,832 --> 01:28:56,902
(A gaze of resentment)

2510
01:28:57,072 --> 01:28:58,401
Let's go.

2511
01:28:58,402 --> 01:28:59,772
(They have to come back and work after a short break.)

2512
01:28:59,902 --> 01:29:01,442
The seagulls are pretty.

2513
01:29:01,942 --> 01:29:03,372
I don't care about things like that.

2514
01:29:04,642 --> 01:29:07,611
(Spacing out)

2515
01:29:07,612 --> 01:29:10,382
(Taking a break)

2516
01:29:10,782 --> 01:29:11,912
Anchovy sauce...

2517
01:29:12,512 --> 01:29:14,922
I should use anchovy sauce sparingly.

2518
01:29:17,692 --> 01:29:19,951
- After working hours...
- They take a break twice.

2519
01:29:19,952 --> 01:29:22,122
Right. So they take a break every two hours.

2520
01:29:22,922 --> 01:29:24,762
If I ever have children,

2521
01:29:24,792 --> 01:29:27,661
I want to tell them to experience this at least once.

2522
01:29:27,662 --> 01:29:29,602
(He wants his future children to try anchovy fishing at least once.)

2523
01:29:29,932 --> 01:29:31,432
(Approaching quietly)

2524
01:29:32,972 --> 01:29:34,242
- What is this?
- A snack.

2525
01:29:35,142 --> 01:29:37,072
Why are you giving us a snack? We should go now.

2526
01:29:38,242 --> 01:29:40,242
Why are you giving us a snack? We should go now.

2527
01:29:40,642 --> 01:29:42,182
- Have a snack.
- Excuse me.

2528
01:29:42,512 --> 01:29:43,911
We should go now. We don't need a snack.

2529
01:29:43,912 --> 01:29:45,082
Why are you being like this today?

2530
01:29:46,512 --> 01:29:48,851
Were you inspired by my "Catch Catch" performance?

2531
01:29:48,852 --> 01:29:50,792
(Were you inspired to live diligently?)

2532
01:29:50,822 --> 01:29:51,991
That's where things went wrong.

2533
01:29:51,992 --> 01:29:54,692
After watching "Catch Catch," people said that...

2534
01:29:54,822 --> 01:29:55,921
they would live diligently.

2535
01:29:55,922 --> 01:29:57,832
No. They have to try this.

2536
01:29:58,432 --> 01:29:59,762
- Seriously.
- Right.

2537
01:30:00,102 --> 01:30:03,161
If you want to realize the value of life, you have to try this.

2538
01:30:03,162 --> 01:30:04,201
That's true.

2539
01:30:04,202 --> 01:30:05,232
Darn it.

2540
01:30:05,702 --> 01:30:08,572
Why did you put precious anchovies in here?

2541
01:30:08,742 --> 01:30:09,772
It has anchovies in it?

2542
01:30:10,042 --> 01:30:12,841
Why are you giving us anchovy rice balls?

2543
01:30:12,842 --> 01:30:14,282
We want you to taste the precious food.

2544
01:30:15,112 --> 01:30:16,582
This is blasphemy.

2545
01:30:17,882 --> 01:30:20,382
Just give us plain rice. We'll rub it over our clothes.

2546
01:30:22,222 --> 01:30:23,392
Eat up and get back to work.

2547
01:30:26,092 --> 01:30:28,761
I didn't work so hard for the "Catch Catch" performance.

2548
01:30:28,762 --> 01:30:29,821
(A bite of an anchovy rice ball eaten after hard labor)

2549
01:30:29,822 --> 01:30:31,462
This is... My goodness.

2550
01:30:31,832 --> 01:30:34,502
- Gosh, this is...
- The anchovy tastes good.

2551
01:30:35,402 --> 01:30:37,772
(Joon has a bite.)

2552
01:30:37,972 --> 01:30:39,672
Did they make Joon's rice ball first?

2553
01:30:40,302 --> 01:30:42,602
- Why?
- His has all the pickled radish.

2554
01:30:42,772 --> 01:30:43,772
(Laughing)

2555
01:30:44,342 --> 01:30:45,641
Is this a random game or what?

2556
01:30:45,642 --> 01:30:46,941
(The fishing makes a single piece of pickled radish feel precious.)

2557
01:30:46,942 --> 01:30:47,981
You're right.

2558
01:30:47,982 --> 01:30:49,182
(The fishing makes a single piece of pickled radish feel precious.)

2559
01:30:49,812 --> 01:30:51,051
(Sniffing)

2560
01:30:51,052 --> 01:30:53,112
Gosh, the smell is so strong.

2561
01:30:53,952 --> 01:30:55,721
Right. Anchovy scales...

2562
01:30:55,722 --> 01:30:57,291
get into my eyes, nostrils, and everything.

2563
01:30:57,292 --> 01:30:58,592
(The scent of anchovies is clinging to their whole body.)

2564
01:30:58,752 --> 01:31:00,621
This is really hard.

2565
01:31:00,622 --> 01:31:04,132
(In the midst of all this, he feels hungry.)

2566
01:31:04,162 --> 01:31:05,431
(Dazed)

2567
01:31:05,432 --> 01:31:07,562
You said Kim Byung Man cried while doing this.

2568
01:31:08,902 --> 01:31:10,371
I understand.

2569
01:31:10,372 --> 01:31:11,431
He had a reason.

2570
01:31:11,432 --> 01:31:13,541
Seriously. At first, I didn't understand...

2571
01:31:13,542 --> 01:31:15,741
that it could be so hard. But that's not it.

2572
01:31:15,742 --> 01:31:18,611
There's something about this that gives a resonance.

2573
01:31:18,612 --> 01:31:20,312
It's not just physically difficult.

2574
01:31:20,912 --> 01:31:23,881
As I did this work, my past days flashed through my mind.

2575
01:31:23,882 --> 01:31:28,152
(A moment that makes you look back on your entire life.)

2576
01:31:28,222 --> 01:31:32,792
But if I lose my tempo, it causes trouble for the others.

2577
01:31:33,192 --> 01:31:35,821
So I can't even complain about how hard it is.

2578
01:31:35,822 --> 01:31:38,432
(A cooperative fishing work makes you unable to give up.)

2579
01:31:38,662 --> 01:31:42,102
It was the hardest thing I've ever done on 2 Days 1 Night.

2580
01:31:43,502 --> 01:31:46,031
It was the worst. It was the hardest.

2581
01:31:46,032 --> 01:31:47,202
You must do it to know.

2582
01:31:47,502 --> 01:31:50,042
I highly recommend this part-time job.

2583
01:31:50,172 --> 01:31:51,742
- Seriously.
- When you need a wake-up call.

2584
01:31:52,212 --> 01:31:54,682
The fishermen said they did this for 4 or 5 hours.

2585
01:31:54,782 --> 01:31:57,682
The time you spent doing that until you were drained...

2586
01:31:58,312 --> 01:31:59,681
was just one hour.

2587
01:31:59,682 --> 01:32:01,352
(They worked 1 out of 4 hours.)

2588
01:32:01,722 --> 01:32:05,322
(Devastated)

2589
01:32:05,522 --> 01:32:08,522
Are the others really having fun? What are they doing?

2590
01:32:09,822 --> 01:32:12,261
You have no idea what they're doing.

2591
01:32:12,262 --> 01:32:13,461
I have zero experience.

2592
01:32:13,462 --> 01:32:15,002
Today, right now,

2593
01:32:15,302 --> 01:32:18,632
they're having as good a time as you had worked hard at work.

2594
01:32:19,502 --> 01:32:20,502
Good for them.

2595
01:32:20,502 --> 01:32:21,502
(Holding back)

2596
01:32:21,602 --> 01:32:22,771
They went biking.

2597
01:32:22,772 --> 01:32:25,112
I feel terrible for wasting...

2598
01:32:25,612 --> 01:32:27,082
I was so arrogant.

2599
01:32:30,282 --> 01:32:31,382
Shall we lie down?

2600
01:32:34,982 --> 01:32:39,452
(Lying on the ground)

2601
01:32:39,592 --> 01:32:40,662
Oh, gosh.

2602
01:32:44,792 --> 01:32:45,962
You know,

2603
01:32:46,332 --> 01:32:49,302
Halli Galli was the most important part.

2604
01:32:49,632 --> 01:32:51,601
Just one game of Halli Galli...

2605
01:32:51,602 --> 01:32:54,002
(One game changed their fates.)

2606
01:32:55,142 --> 01:32:59,842
(Reusing the rice ball packaging to hide from the sun)

2607
01:32:59,942 --> 01:33:02,842
We'll leave in ten minutes.

2608
01:33:03,112 --> 01:33:04,151
Okay.

2609
01:33:04,152 --> 01:33:11,592
(They fell fast asleep on the ground.)

2610
01:33:11,752 --> 01:33:13,562
(Next episode)

2611
01:33:13,962 --> 01:33:17,432
(The working holiday is not yet over.)

2612
01:33:18,262 --> 01:33:21,232
(The members are abandoned somewhere.)

2613
01:33:21,702 --> 01:33:25,302
(If they can't reach the base camp before the time is up,)

2614
01:33:25,632 --> 01:33:28,842
(they all go fishing.)

2615
01:33:29,502 --> 01:33:31,912
(To end the torment...)

2616
01:33:32,212 --> 01:33:35,712
(they run frantically.)

2617
01:33:36,012 --> 01:33:40,322
(Can they secure their holiday?)

2618
01:33:41,782 --> 01:33:46,292
(Our forever youngest member Seon Ho is graduating.)

2619
01:33:46,992 --> 01:33:52,132
(The others prepare a midnight surprise for him.)

2620
01:33:53,602 --> 01:33:55,701
(It's the last night...)

2621
01:33:55,702 --> 01:33:58,272
(they thought wouldn't come.)

2622
01:33:58,902 --> 01:34:00,541
(Our forever youngest member)

2623
01:34:00,542 --> 01:34:02,871
(Thank you for the happy times.)

2624
01:34:02,872 --> 01:34:04,442
(You're the best youngest member, Seon Ho.)

2625
01:34:04,842 --> 01:34:05,842
I love you.

2626
01:34:05,843 --> 01:34:07,482
(See you next week.)
